9// This file implements semantic analysis for cast expressions, including
10// 1) C-style casts like '(int) x'
11// 2) C++ functional casts like 'int(x)'
12// 3) C++ named casts like 'static_cast<int>(x)'

33enum TryCastResult {
34 TC_NotApplicable, ///< The cast method is not applicable.
35 TC_Success, ///< The cast method is appropriate and successful.
36 TC_Extension, ///< The cast method is appropriate and accepted as a
37 ///< language extension.
38 TC_Failed ///< The cast method is appropriate, but failed. A
39 ///< diagnostic has been emitted.
40};
41
42static bool isValidCast(TryCastResult TCR) {
43 return TCR == TC_Success || TCR == TC_Extension;
44}
45
46enum CastType {
47 CT_Const, ///< const_cast
48 CT_Static, ///< static_cast
49 CT_Reinterpret, ///< reinterpret_cast
50 CT_Dynamic, ///< dynamic_cast
51 CT_CStyle, ///< (Type)expr
52 CT_Functional ///< Type(expr)
53};

58namespace {
59 struct CastOperation {
60 CastOperation(Sema &S, QualType destType, ExprResult src)
61 : Self(S), SrcExpr(src), DestType(destType),
62 ResultType(destType.getNonLValueExprType(S.Context)),
63 ValueKind(Expr::getValueKindForType(destType)),
64 Kind(CK_Dependent), IsARCUnbridgedCast(false) {
65
66 if (const BuiltinType *placeholder =
67 src.get()->getType()->getAsPlaceholderType()) {
68 PlaceholderKind = placeholder->getKind();
69 } else {
70 PlaceholderKind = (BuiltinType::Kind) 0;
71 }
72 }
73
74 Sema &Self;
75 ExprResult SrcExpr;
76 QualType DestType;
77 QualType ResultType;
78 ExprValueKind ValueKind;
79 CastKind Kind;
80 BuiltinType::Kind PlaceholderKind;
81 CXXCastPath BasePath;
82 bool IsARCUnbridgedCast;
83
84 SourceRange OpRange;
85 SourceRange DestRange;
86
87 // Top-level semantics-checking routines.
88 void CheckConstCast();
89 void CheckReinterpretCast();
90 void CheckStaticCast();
91 void CheckDynamicCast();
92 void CheckCXXCStyleCast(bool FunctionalCast, bool ListInitialization);
93 void CheckCStyleCast();

95 void updatePartOfExplicitCastFlags(CastExpr *CE) {
96 // Walk down from the CE to the OrigSrcExpr, and mark all immediate
97 // ImplicitCastExpr's as being part of ExplicitCastExpr. The original CE
98 // (which is a ExplicitCastExpr), and the OrigSrcExpr are not touched.
99 for (; auto *ICE = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(CE->getSubExpr()); CE = ICE)
100 ICE->setIsPartOfExplicitCast(true);
101 }
102
103 /// Complete an apparently-successful cast operation that yields
104 /// the given expression.
105 ExprResult complete(CastExpr *castExpr) {
106 SourceRange CastRange = OpRange;
107 if (CXXNamedCastExpr* CNC = dyn_cast<CXXNamedCastExpr>(castExpr)) {
108 CastRange = CNC->getAngleBrackets();
109 }
110 if (!isa<CXXConstructExpr>(SrcExpr.get())) {
111 CastKind CK = DiagnoseCapabilityToIntCast(Self, CastRange,
112 SrcExpr.get(), DestType);
113 // Make sure that the types actually match:
114 if (CK == CK_CHERICapabilityToPointer && DestType->isReferenceType()) {
115 // return ExprError();
116 }
117 }
118
119
120 // If this is an unbridged cast, wrap the result in an implicit
121 // cast that yields the unbridged-cast placeholder type.
122 if (IsARCUnbridgedCast) {
123 castExpr = ImplicitCastExpr::Create(Self.Context,
124 Self.Context.ARCUnbridgedCastTy,
125 CK_Dependent, castExpr, nullptr,
126 castExpr->getValueKind());
127 }
128 updatePartOfExplicitCastFlags(castExpr);
129 return castExpr;
130 }

134 /// Try to handle the given placeholder expression kind. Return
135 /// true if the source expression has the appropriate placeholder
136 /// kind. A placeholder can only be claimed once.
137 bool claimPlaceholder(BuiltinType::Kind K) {
138 if (PlaceholderKind != K) return false;
139
140 PlaceholderKind = (BuiltinType::Kind) 0;
141 return true;
142 }
143
144 bool isPlaceholder() const {
145 return PlaceholderKind != 0;
146 }
147 bool isPlaceholder(BuiltinType::Kind K) const {
148 return PlaceholderKind == K;
149 }

151 // Language specific cast restrictions for address spaces.
152 void checkAddressSpaceCast(QualType SrcType, QualType DestType);
153
154 void checkCastAlign() {
155 Self.CheckCastAlign(SrcExpr.get(), DestType, OpRange);
156 }
157
158 void checkObjCConversion(Sema::CheckedConversionKind CCK) {
159 assert(Self.getLangOpts().allowsNonTrivialObjCLifetimeQualifiers());
160
161 Expr *src = SrcExpr.get();
162 if (Self.CheckObjCConversion(OpRange, DestType, src, CCK) ==
163 Sema::ACR_unbridged)
164 IsARCUnbridgedCast = true;
165 SrcExpr = src;
166 }
167
168 /// Check for and handle non-overload placeholder expressions.
169 void checkNonOverloadPlaceholders() {
170 if (!isPlaceholder() || isPlaceholder(BuiltinType::Overload))
171 return;
172
173 SrcExpr = Self.CheckPlaceholderExpr(SrcExpr.get());
174 if (SrcExpr.isInvalid())
175 return;
176 PlaceholderKind = (BuiltinType::Kind) 0;
177 }
178 };

250/// ActOnCXXNamedCast - Parse {dynamic,static,reinterpret,const}_cast's.
251ExprResult
252Sema::ActOnCXXNamedCast(SourceLocation OpLoc, tok::TokenKind Kind,
253 SourceLocation LAngleBracketLoc, Declarator &D,
254 SourceLocation RAngleBracketLoc,
255 SourceLocation LParenLoc, Expr *E,
256 SourceLocation RParenLoc) {
257
258 assert(!D.isInvalidType());
259
260 TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = GetTypeForDeclaratorCast(D, E->getType());
261 if (D.isInvalidType())
262 return ExprError();
263
264 if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
265 // Check that there are no default arguments (C++ only).
266 CheckExtraCXXDefaultArguments(D);
267 }
268
269 return BuildCXXNamedCast(OpLoc, Kind, TInfo, E,
270 SourceRange(LAngleBracketLoc, RAngleBracketLoc),
271 SourceRange(LParenLoc, RParenLoc));
272}
273
274ExprResult
275Sema::BuildCXXNamedCast(SourceLocation OpLoc, tok::TokenKind Kind,
276 TypeSourceInfo *DestTInfo, Expr *E,
277 SourceRange AngleBrackets, SourceRange Parens) {
278 ExprResult Ex = E;
279 QualType DestType = DestTInfo->getType();
280
281 // If the type is dependent, we won't do the semantic analysis now.
282 bool TypeDependent =
283 DestType->isDependentType() || Ex.get()->isTypeDependent();
284
285 CastOperation Op(*this, DestType, E);
286 Op.OpRange = SourceRange(OpLoc, Parens.getEnd());
287 Op.DestRange = AngleBrackets;
288
289 switch (Kind) {
290 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown C++ cast!");
291
292 case tok::kw_const_cast:
293 if (!TypeDependent) {
294 Op.CheckConstCast();
295 if (Op.SrcExpr.isInvalid())
296 return ExprError();
297 DiscardMisalignedMemberAddress(DestType.getTypePtr(), E);
298 }
299 return Op.complete(CXXConstCastExpr::Create(Context, Op.ResultType,
300 Op.ValueKind, Op.SrcExpr.get(), DestTInfo,
301 OpLoc, Parens.getEnd(),
302 AngleBrackets));
303
304 case tok::kw_dynamic_cast: {
305 // OpenCL C++ 1.0 s2.9: dynamic_cast is not supported.
306 if (getLangOpts().OpenCLCPlusPlus) {
307 return ExprError(Diag(OpLoc, diag::err_openclcxx_not_supported)
308 << "dynamic_cast");
309 }
310
311 if (!TypeDependent) {
312 Op.CheckDynamicCast();
313 if (Op.SrcExpr.isInvalid())
314 return ExprError();
315 }
316 return Op.complete(CXXDynamicCastExpr::Create(Context, Op.ResultType,
317 Op.ValueKind, Op.Kind, Op.SrcExpr.get(),
318 &Op.BasePath, DestTInfo,
319 OpLoc, Parens.getEnd(),
320 AngleBrackets));
321 }
322 case tok::kw_reinterpret_cast: {
323 if (!TypeDependent) {
324 Op.CheckReinterpretCast();
325 if (Op.SrcExpr.isInvalid())
326 return ExprError();
327 DiscardMisalignedMemberAddress(DestType.getTypePtr(), E);
328 }
329 return Op.complete(CXXReinterpretCastExpr::Create(Context, Op.ResultType,
330 Op.ValueKind, Op.Kind, Op.SrcExpr.get(),
331 nullptr, DestTInfo, OpLoc,
332 Parens.getEnd(),
333 AngleBrackets));
334 }
335 case tok::kw_static_cast: {
336 if (!TypeDependent) {
337 Op.CheckStaticCast();
338 if (Op.SrcExpr.isInvalid())
339 return ExprError();
340 DiscardMisalignedMemberAddress(DestType.getTypePtr(), E);
341 }
342
343 return Op.complete(CXXStaticCastExpr::Create(Context, Op.ResultType,
344 Op.ValueKind, Op.Kind, Op.SrcExpr.get(),
345 &Op.BasePath, DestTInfo,
346 OpLoc, Parens.getEnd(),
347 AngleBrackets));
348 }
349 }

352/// Try to diagnose a failed overloaded cast. Returns true if
353/// diagnostics were emitted.
354static bool tryDiagnoseOverloadedCast(Sema &S, CastType CT,
355 SourceRange range, Expr *src,
356 QualType destType,
357 bool listInitialization) {
358 switch (CT) {
359 // These cast kinds don't consider user-defined conversions.
360 case CT_Const:
361 case CT_Reinterpret:
362 case CT_Dynamic:
363 return false;
364
365 // These do.
366 case CT_Static:
367 case CT_CStyle:
368 case CT_Functional:
369 break;
370 }
371
372 QualType srcType = src->getType();
373 if (!destType->isRecordType() && !srcType->isRecordType())
374 return false;
375
376 InitializedEntity entity = InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(destType);
377 InitializationKind initKind
378 = (CT == CT_CStyle)? InitializationKind::CreateCStyleCast(range.getBegin(),
379 range, listInitialization)
380 : (CT == CT_Functional)? InitializationKind::CreateFunctionalCast(range,
381 listInitialization)
382 : InitializationKind::CreateCast(/*type range?*/ range);
383 InitializationSequence sequence(S, entity, initKind, src);
384
385 assert(sequence.Failed() && "initialization succeeded on second try?");
386 switch (sequence.getFailureKind()) {
387 default: return false;
388
389 case InitializationSequence::FK_ConstructorOverloadFailed:
390 case InitializationSequence::FK_UserConversionOverloadFailed:
391 break;
392 }
393
394 OverloadCandidateSet &candidates = sequence.getFailedCandidateSet();
395
396 unsigned msg = 0;
397 OverloadCandidateDisplayKind howManyCandidates = OCD_AllCandidates;
398
399 switch (sequence.getFailedOverloadResult()) {
400 case OR_Success: llvm_unreachable("successful failed overload");
401 case OR_No_Viable_Function:
402 if (candidates.empty())
403 msg = diag::err_ovl_no_conversion_in_cast;
404 else
405 msg = diag::err_ovl_no_viable_conversion_in_cast;
406 howManyCandidates = OCD_AllCandidates;
407 break;
408
409 case OR_Ambiguous:
410 msg = diag::err_ovl_ambiguous_conversion_in_cast;
411 howManyCandidates = OCD_ViableCandidates;
412 break;
413
414 case OR_Deleted:
415 msg = diag::err_ovl_deleted_conversion_in_cast;
416 howManyCandidates = OCD_ViableCandidates;
417 break;
418 }
419
420 candidates.NoteCandidates(
421 PartialDiagnosticAt(range.getBegin(),
422 S.PDiag(msg) << CT << srcType << destType << range
423 << src->getSourceRange()),
424 S, howManyCandidates, src);
425
426 return true;
427}
428
429/// Diagnose a failed cast.
430static void diagnoseBadCast(Sema &S, unsigned msg, CastType castType,
431 SourceRange opRange, Expr *src, QualType destType,
432 bool listInitialization) {
433 if (msg == diag::err_bad_cxx_cast_generic &&
434 tryDiagnoseOverloadedCast(S, castType, opRange, src, destType,
435 listInitialization))
436 return;
437
438 S.Diag(opRange.getBegin(), msg) << castType
439 << src->getType() << destType << opRange << src->getSourceRange();
440
441 // Detect if both types are (ptr to) class, and note any incompleteness.
442 int DifferentPtrness = 0;
443 QualType From = destType;
444 if (auto Ptr = From->getAs<PointerType>()) {
445 From = Ptr->getPointeeType();
446 DifferentPtrness++;
447 }
448 QualType To = src->getType();
449 if (auto Ptr = To->getAs<PointerType>()) {
450 To = Ptr->getPointeeType();
451 DifferentPtrness--;
452 }
453 if (!DifferentPtrness) {
454 auto RecFrom = From->getAs<RecordType>();
455 auto RecTo = To->getAs<RecordType>();
456 if (RecFrom && RecTo) {
457 auto DeclFrom = RecFrom->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
458 if (!DeclFrom->isCompleteDefinition())
459 S.Diag(DeclFrom->getLocation(), diag::note_type_incomplete)
460 << DeclFrom->getDeclName();
461 auto DeclTo = RecTo->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
462 if (!DeclTo->isCompleteDefinition())
463 S.Diag(DeclTo->getLocation(), diag::note_type_incomplete)
464 << DeclTo->getDeclName();
465 }
466 }

469namespace {
470/// The kind of unwrapping we did when determining whether a conversion casts
471/// away constness.
472enum CastAwayConstnessKind {
473 /// The conversion does not cast away constness.
474 CACK_None = 0,
475 /// We unwrapped similar types.
476 CACK_Similar = 1,
477 /// We unwrapped dissimilar types with similar representations (eg, a pointer
478 /// versus an Objective-C object pointer).
479 CACK_SimilarKind = 2,
480 /// We unwrapped representationally-unrelated types, such as a pointer versus
481 /// a pointer-to-member.
482 CACK_Incoherent = 3,
483};
484}
485
486/// Unwrap one level of types for CastsAwayConstness.
487///
488/// Like Sema::UnwrapSimilarTypes, this removes one level of indirection from
489/// both types, provided that they're both pointer-like or array-like. Unlike
490/// the Sema function, doesn't care if the unwrapped pieces are related.
491///
492/// This function may remove additional levels as necessary for correctness:
493/// the resulting T1 is unwrapped sufficiently that it is never an array type,
494/// so that its qualifiers can be directly compared to those of T2 (which will
495/// have the combined set of qualifiers from all indermediate levels of T2),
496/// as (effectively) required by [expr.const.cast]p7 replacing T1's qualifiers
497/// with those from T2.
498static CastAwayConstnessKind
499unwrapCastAwayConstnessLevel(ASTContext &Context, QualType &T1, QualType &T2) {
500 enum { None, Ptr, MemPtr, BlockPtr, Array };
501 auto Classify = [](QualType T) {
502 if (T->isAnyPointerType()) return Ptr;
503 if (T->isMemberPointerType()) return MemPtr;
504 if (T->isBlockPointerType()) return BlockPtr;
505 // We somewhat-arbitrarily don't look through VLA types here. This is at
506 // least consistent with the behavior of UnwrapSimilarTypes.
507 if (T->isConstantArrayType() || T->isIncompleteArrayType()) return Array;
508 return None;
509 };
510
511 auto Unwrap = [&](QualType T) {
512 if (auto *AT = Context.getAsArrayType(T))
513 return AT->getElementType();
514 return T->getPointeeType();
515 };
516
517 CastAwayConstnessKind Kind;
518
519 if (T2->isReferenceType()) {
520 // Special case: if the destination type is a reference type, unwrap it as
521 // the first level. (The source will have been an lvalue expression in this
522 // case, so there is no corresponding "reference to" in T1 to remove.) This
523 // simulates removing a "pointer to" from both sides.
524 T2 = T2->getPointeeType();
525 Kind = CastAwayConstnessKind::CACK_Similar;
526 } else if (Context.UnwrapSimilarTypes(T1, T2)) {
527 Kind = CastAwayConstnessKind::CACK_Similar;
528 } else {
529 // Try unwrapping mismatching levels.
530 int T1Class = Classify(T1);
531 if (T1Class == None)
532 return CastAwayConstnessKind::CACK_None;
533
534 int T2Class = Classify(T2);
535 if (T2Class == None)
536 return CastAwayConstnessKind::CACK_None;
537
538 T1 = Unwrap(T1);
539 T2 = Unwrap(T2);
540 Kind = T1Class == T2Class ? CastAwayConstnessKind::CACK_SimilarKind
541 : CastAwayConstnessKind::CACK_Incoherent;
542 }
543
544 // We've unwrapped at least one level. If the resulting T1 is a (possibly
545 // multidimensional) array type, any qualifier on any matching layer of
546 // T2 is considered to correspond to T1. Decompose down to the element
547 // type of T1 so that we can compare properly.
548 while (true) {
549 Context.UnwrapSimilarArrayTypes(T1, T2);
550
551 if (Classify(T1) != Array)
552 break;
553
554 auto T2Class = Classify(T2);
555 if (T2Class == None)
556 break;
557
558 if (T2Class != Array)
559 Kind = CastAwayConstnessKind::CACK_Incoherent;
560 else if (Kind != CastAwayConstnessKind::CACK_Incoherent)
561 Kind = CastAwayConstnessKind::CACK_SimilarKind;
562
563 T1 = Unwrap(T1);
564 T2 = Unwrap(T2).withCVRQualifiers(T2.getCVRQualifiers());
565 }
566
567 return Kind;
568}
569
570/// Check if the pointer conversion from SrcType to DestType casts away
571/// constness as defined in C++ [expr.const.cast]. This is used by the cast
572/// checkers. Both arguments must denote pointer (possibly to member) types.
573///
574/// \param CheckCVR Whether to check for const/volatile/restrict qualifiers.
575/// \param CheckObjCLifetime Whether to check Objective-C lifetime qualifiers.
576static CastAwayConstnessKind
577CastsAwayConstness(Sema &Self, QualType SrcType, QualType DestType,
578 bool CheckCVR, bool CheckObjCLifetime,
579 QualType *TheOffendingSrcType = nullptr,
580 QualType *TheOffendingDestType = nullptr,
581 Qualifiers *CastAwayQualifiers = nullptr) {
582 // If the only checking we care about is for Objective-C lifetime qualifiers,
583 // and we're not in ObjC mode, there's nothing to check.
584 if (!CheckCVR && CheckObjCLifetime && !Self.Context.getLangOpts().ObjC)
585 return CastAwayConstnessKind::CACK_None;
586
587 if (!DestType->isReferenceType()) {
588 assert((SrcType->isAnyPointerType() || SrcType->isMemberPointerType() ||
589 SrcType->isBlockPointerType()) &&
590 "Source type is not pointer or pointer to member.");
591 assert((DestType->isAnyPointerType() || DestType->isMemberPointerType() ||
592 DestType->isBlockPointerType()) &&
593 "Destination type is not pointer or pointer to member.");
594 }
595
596 QualType UnwrappedSrcType = Self.Context.getCanonicalType(SrcType),
597 UnwrappedDestType = Self.Context.getCanonicalType(DestType);
598
599 // Find the qualifiers. We only care about cvr-qualifiers for the
600 // purpose of this check, because other qualifiers (address spaces,
601 // Objective-C GC, etc.) are part of the type's identity.
602 QualType PrevUnwrappedSrcType = UnwrappedSrcType;
603 QualType PrevUnwrappedDestType = UnwrappedDestType;
604 auto WorstKind = CastAwayConstnessKind::CACK_Similar;
605 bool AllConstSoFar = true;
606 while (auto Kind = unwrapCastAwayConstnessLevel(
607 Self.Context, UnwrappedSrcType, UnwrappedDestType)) {
608 // Track the worst kind of unwrap we needed to do before we found a
609 // problem.
610 if (Kind > WorstKind)
611 WorstKind = Kind;
612
613 // Determine the relevant qualifiers at this level.
614 Qualifiers SrcQuals, DestQuals;
615 Self.Context.getUnqualifiedArrayType(UnwrappedSrcType, SrcQuals);
616 Self.Context.getUnqualifiedArrayType(UnwrappedDestType, DestQuals);
617
618 // We do not meaningfully track object const-ness of Objective-C object
619 // types. Remove const from the source type if either the source or
620 // the destination is an Objective-C object type.
621 if (UnwrappedSrcType->isObjCObjectType() ||
622 UnwrappedDestType->isObjCObjectType())
623 SrcQuals.removeConst();
624
625 if (CheckCVR) {
626 Qualifiers SrcCvrQuals =
627 Qualifiers::fromCVRMask(SrcQuals.getCVRQualifiers());
628 Qualifiers DestCvrQuals =
629 Qualifiers::fromCVRMask(DestQuals.getCVRQualifiers());
630
631 if (SrcCvrQuals != DestCvrQuals) {
632 if (CastAwayQualifiers)
633 *CastAwayQualifiers = SrcCvrQuals - DestCvrQuals;
634
635 // If we removed a cvr-qualifier, this is casting away 'constness'.
636 if (!DestCvrQuals.compatiblyIncludes(SrcCvrQuals)) {
637 if (TheOffendingSrcType)
638 *TheOffendingSrcType = PrevUnwrappedSrcType;
639 if (TheOffendingDestType)
640 *TheOffendingDestType = PrevUnwrappedDestType;
641 return WorstKind;
642 }
643
644 // If any prior level was not 'const', this is also casting away
645 // 'constness'. We noted the outermost type missing a 'const' already.
646 if (!AllConstSoFar)
647 return WorstKind;
648 }
649 }
650
651 if (CheckObjCLifetime &&
652 !DestQuals.compatiblyIncludesObjCLifetime(SrcQuals))
653 return WorstKind;
654
655 // If we found our first non-const-qualified type, this may be the place
656 // where things start to go wrong.
657 if (AllConstSoFar && !DestQuals.hasConst()) {
658 AllConstSoFar = false;
659 if (TheOffendingSrcType)
660 *TheOffendingSrcType = PrevUnwrappedSrcType;
661 if (TheOffendingDestType)
662 *TheOffendingDestType = PrevUnwrappedDestType;
663 }
664
665 PrevUnwrappedSrcType = UnwrappedSrcType;
666 PrevUnwrappedDestType = UnwrappedDestType;
667 }
668
669 return CastAwayConstnessKind::CACK_None;
670}
671
672static TryCastResult getCastAwayConstnessCastKind(CastAwayConstnessKind CACK,
673 unsigned &DiagID) {
674 switch (CACK) {
675 case CastAwayConstnessKind::CACK_None:
676 llvm_unreachable("did not cast away constness");
677
678 case CastAwayConstnessKind::CACK_Similar:
679 // FIXME: Accept these as an extension too?
680 case CastAwayConstnessKind::CACK_SimilarKind:
681 DiagID = diag::err_bad_cxx_cast_qualifiers_away;
682 return TC_Failed;
683
684 case CastAwayConstnessKind::CACK_Incoherent:
685 DiagID = diag::ext_bad_cxx_cast_qualifiers_away_incoherent;
686 return TC_Extension;
687 }
688
689 llvm_unreachable("unexpected cast away constness kind");
690}
691
692static bool IsBadCheriReferenceCast(const ReferenceType *Dest, Expr *SrcExpr,
693 ASTContext &Ctx) {
694 if (Ctx.getLangOpts().getCheriCapConversion() == LangOptions::CapConv_Ignore)
695 return false;
696 bool SrcIsCapRef = Ctx.getTargetInfo().areAllPointersCapabilities();
697 if (auto SrcRef = SrcExpr->getRealReferenceType(Ctx)->getAs<ReferenceType>())
698 SrcIsCapRef = SrcRef->isCHERICapability();
699 return Dest->isCHERICapability() != SrcIsCapRef;
700}
701
702/// CheckDynamicCast - Check that a dynamic_cast\<DestType\>(SrcExpr) is valid.
703/// Refer to C++ 5.2.7 for details. Dynamic casts are used mostly for runtime-
704/// checked downcasts in class hierarchies.
705void CastOperation::CheckDynamicCast() {
706 if (ValueKind == VK_RValue)
707 SrcExpr = Self.DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(SrcExpr.get());
708 else if (isPlaceholder())
709 SrcExpr = Self.CheckPlaceholderExpr(SrcExpr.get());
710 if (SrcExpr.isInvalid()) // if conversion failed, don't report another error
711 return;
712
713 QualType OrigSrcType = SrcExpr.get()->getType();
714 QualType DestType = Self.Context.getCanonicalType(this->DestType);
715
716 // C++ 5.2.7p1: T shall be a pointer or reference to a complete class type,
717 // or "pointer to cv void".
718
719 QualType DestPointee;
720 const PointerType *DestPointer = DestType->getAs<PointerType>();
721 const ReferenceType *DestReference = nullptr;
722 if (DestPointer) {
723 DestPointee = DestPointer->getPointeeType();
724 } else if ((DestReference = DestType->getAs<ReferenceType>())) {
725 DestPointee = DestReference->getPointeeType();
726 } else {
727 Self.Diag(OpRange.getBegin(), diag::err_bad_dynamic_cast_not_ref_or_ptr)
728 << this->DestType << DestRange;
729 SrcExpr = ExprError();
730 return;
731 }
732
733 const RecordType *DestRecord = DestPointee->getAs<RecordType>();
734 if (DestPointee->isVoidType()) {
735 assert(DestPointer && "Reference to void is not possible");
736 } else if (DestRecord) {
737 if (Self.RequireCompleteType(OpRange.getBegin(), DestPointee,
738 diag::err_bad_dynamic_cast_incomplete,
739 DestRange)) {
740 SrcExpr = ExprError();
741 return;
742 }
743 } else {
744 Self.Diag(OpRange.getBegin(), diag::err_bad_dynamic_cast_not_class)
745 << DestPointee.getUnqualifiedType() << DestRange;
746 SrcExpr = ExprError();
747 return;
748 }
749
750 // C++0x 5.2.7p2: If T is a pointer type, v shall be an rvalue of a pointer to
751 // complete class type, [...]. If T is an lvalue reference type, v shall be
752 // an lvalue of a complete class type, [...]. If T is an rvalue reference
753 // type, v shall be an expression having a complete class type, [...]
754 QualType SrcType = Self.Context.getCanonicalType(OrigSrcType);
755 QualType SrcPointee;
756 if (DestPointer) {
757 if (const PointerType *SrcPointer = SrcType->getAs<PointerType>()) {
758 SrcPointee = SrcPointer->getPointeeType();
759 } else {
760 Self.Diag(OpRange.getBegin(), diag::err_bad_dynamic_cast_not_ptr)
761 << OrigSrcType << SrcExpr.get()->getSourceRange();
762 SrcExpr = ExprError();
763 return;
764 }
765 } else if (DestReference->isLValueReferenceType()) {
766 if (!SrcExpr.get()->isLValue()) {
767 Self.Diag(OpRange.getBegin(), diag::err_bad_cxx_cast_rvalue)
768 << CT_Dynamic << OrigSrcType << this->DestType << OpRange;
769 }
770 SrcPointee = SrcType;
771 } else {
772 // If we're dynamic_casting from a prvalue to an rvalue reference, we need
773 // to materialize the prvalue before we bind the reference to it.
774 if (SrcExpr.get()->isRValue())
775 SrcExpr = Self.CreateMaterializeTemporaryExpr(
776 SrcType, SrcExpr.get(), /*IsLValueReference*/ false);
777 SrcPointee = SrcType;
778 }
779
780 const RecordType *SrcRecord = SrcPointee->getAs<RecordType>();
781 if (SrcRecord) {
782 if (Self.RequireCompleteType(OpRange.getBegin(), SrcPointee,
783 diag::err_bad_dynamic_cast_incomplete,
784 SrcExpr.get())) {
785 SrcExpr = ExprError();
786 return;
787 }
788 } else {
789 Self.Diag(OpRange.getBegin(), diag::err_bad_dynamic_cast_not_class)
790 << SrcPointee.getUnqualifiedType() << SrcExpr.get()->getSourceRange();
791 SrcExpr = ExprError();
792 return;
793 }
794
795 assert((DestPointer || DestReference) &&
796 "Bad destination non-ptr/ref slipped through.");
797 assert((DestRecord || DestPointee->isVoidType()) &&
798 "Bad destination pointee slipped through.");
799 assert(SrcRecord && "Bad source pointee slipped through.");
800
801 // C++ 5.2.7p1: The dynamic_cast operator shall not cast away constness.
802 if (!DestPointee.isAtLeastAsQualifiedAs(SrcPointee)) {
803 Self.Diag(OpRange.getBegin(), diag::err_bad_cxx_cast_qualifiers_away)
804 << CT_Dynamic << OrigSrcType << this->DestType << OpRange;
805 SrcExpr = ExprError();
806 return;
807 }
808
809 // Check that the dynamic cast doesn't change the capability qualifier
810 if (DestReference && IsBadCheriReferenceCast(DestReference, SrcExpr.get(),
811 Self.getASTContext())) {
812 Self.Diag(OpRange.getBegin(), diag::err_bad_cxx_reference_cast_capability_qualifier)
813 << CT_Dynamic << 0 << DestType;
814 SrcExpr = ExprError();
815 return;
816 }
817
818 // C++ 5.2.7p3: If the type of v is the same as the required result type,
819 // [except for cv].
820 if (DestRecord == SrcRecord) {
821 Kind = CK_NoOp;
822 return;
823 }
824
825 // C++ 5.2.7p5
826 // Upcasts are resolved statically.
827 if (DestRecord &&
828 Self.IsDerivedFrom(OpRange.getBegin(), SrcPointee, DestPointee)) {
829 if (Self.CheckDerivedToBaseConversion(SrcPointee, DestPointee,
830 OpRange.getBegin(), OpRange,
831 &BasePath)) {
832 SrcExpr = ExprError();
833 return;
834 }
835
836 Kind = CK_DerivedToBase;
837 return;
838 }
839
840 // C++ 5.2.7p6: Otherwise, v shall be [polymorphic].
841 const RecordDecl *SrcDecl = SrcRecord->getDecl()->getDefinition();
842 assert(SrcDecl && "Definition missing");
843 if (!cast<CXXRecordDecl>(SrcDecl)->isPolymorphic()) {
844 Self.Diag(OpRange.getBegin(), diag::err_bad_dynamic_cast_not_polymorphic)
845 << SrcPointee.getUnqualifiedType() << SrcExpr.get()->getSourceRange();
846 SrcExpr = ExprError();
847 }
848
849 // dynamic_cast is not available with -fno-rtti.
850 // As an exception, dynamic_cast to void* is available because it doesn't
851 // use RTTI.
852 if (!Self.getLangOpts().RTTI && !DestPointee->isVoidType()) {
853 Self.Diag(OpRange.getBegin(), diag::err_no_dynamic_cast_with_fno_rtti);
854 SrcExpr = ExprError();
855 return;
856 }
857
858 // Done. Everything else is run-time checks.
859 Kind = CK_Dynamic;
860}
861
862/// CheckConstCast - Check that a const_cast\<DestType\>(SrcExpr) is valid.
863/// Refer to C++ 5.2.11 for details. const_cast is typically used in code
864/// like this:
865/// const char *str = "literal";
866/// legacy_function(const_cast\<char*\>(str));
867void CastOperation::CheckConstCast() {
868 if (ValueKind == VK_RValue)
869 SrcExpr = Self.DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(SrcExpr.get());
870 else if (isPlaceholder())
871 SrcExpr = Self.CheckPlaceholderExpr(SrcExpr.get());
872 if (SrcExpr.isInvalid()) // if conversion failed, don't report another error
873 return;
874
875 unsigned msg = diag::err_bad_cxx_cast_generic;
876 auto TCR = TryConstCast(Self, SrcExpr, DestType, /*CStyle*/ false, msg);
877 if (TCR != TC_Success && msg != 0) {
878 Self.Diag(OpRange.getBegin(), msg) << CT_Const
879 << SrcExpr.get()->getType() << DestType << OpRange;
880 }
881 if (!isValidCast(TCR))
882 SrcExpr = ExprError();
883}
884
885/// Check that a reinterpret_cast\<DestType\>(SrcExpr) is not used as upcast
886/// or downcast between respective pointers or references.
887static void DiagnoseReinterpretUpDownCast(Sema &Self, const Expr *SrcExpr,
888 QualType DestType,
889 SourceRange OpRange) {
890 QualType SrcType = SrcExpr->getType();
891 // When casting from pointer or reference, get pointee type; use original
892 // type otherwise.
893 const CXXRecordDecl *SrcPointeeRD = SrcType->getPointeeCXXRecordDecl();
894 const CXXRecordDecl *SrcRD =
895 SrcPointeeRD ? SrcPointeeRD : SrcType->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
896
897 // Examining subobjects for records is only possible if the complete and
898 // valid definition is available. Also, template instantiation is not
899 // allowed here.
900 if (!SrcRD || !SrcRD->isCompleteDefinition() || SrcRD->isInvalidDecl())
901 return;
902
903 const CXXRecordDecl *DestRD = DestType->getPointeeCXXRecordDecl();
904
905 if (!DestRD || !DestRD->isCompleteDefinition() || DestRD->isInvalidDecl())
906 return;
907
908 enum {
909 ReinterpretUpcast,
910 ReinterpretDowncast
911 } ReinterpretKind;
912
913 CXXBasePaths BasePaths;
914
915 if (SrcRD->isDerivedFrom(DestRD, BasePaths))
916 ReinterpretKind = ReinterpretUpcast;
917 else if (DestRD->isDerivedFrom(SrcRD, BasePaths))
918 ReinterpretKind = ReinterpretDowncast;
919 else
920 return;
921
922 bool VirtualBase = true;
923 bool NonZeroOffset = false;
924 for (CXXBasePaths::const_paths_iterator I = BasePaths.begin(),
925 E = BasePaths.end();
926 I != E; ++I) {
927 const CXXBasePath &Path = *I;
928 CharUnits Offset = CharUnits::Zero();
929 bool IsVirtual = false;
930 for (CXXBasePath::const_iterator IElem = Path.begin(), EElem = Path.end();
931 IElem != EElem; ++IElem) {
932 IsVirtual = IElem->Base->isVirtual();
933 if (IsVirtual)
934 break;
935 const CXXRecordDecl *BaseRD = IElem->Base->getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
936 assert(BaseRD && "Base type should be a valid unqualified class type");
937 // Don't check if any base has invalid declaration or has no definition
938 // since it has no layout info.
939 const CXXRecordDecl *Class = IElem->Class,
940 *ClassDefinition = Class->getDefinition();
941 if (Class->isInvalidDecl() || !ClassDefinition ||
942 !ClassDefinition->isCompleteDefinition())
943 return;
944
945 const ASTRecordLayout &DerivedLayout =
946 Self.Context.getASTRecordLayout(Class);
947 Offset += DerivedLayout.getBaseClassOffset(BaseRD);
948 }
949 if (!IsVirtual) {
950 // Don't warn if any path is a non-virtually derived base at offset zero.
951 if (Offset.isZero())
952 return;
953 // Offset makes sense only for non-virtual bases.
954 else
955 NonZeroOffset = true;
956 }
957 VirtualBase = VirtualBase && IsVirtual;
958 }
959
960 (void) NonZeroOffset; // Silence set but not used warning.
961 assert((VirtualBase || NonZeroOffset) &&
962 "Should have returned if has non-virtual base with zero offset");
963
964 QualType BaseType =
965 ReinterpretKind == ReinterpretUpcast? DestType : SrcType;
966 QualType DerivedType =
967 ReinterpretKind == ReinterpretUpcast? SrcType : DestType;
968
969 SourceLocation BeginLoc = OpRange.getBegin();
970 Self.Diag(BeginLoc, diag::warn_reinterpret_different_from_static)
971 << DerivedType << BaseType << !VirtualBase << int(ReinterpretKind)
972 << OpRange;
973 Self.Diag(BeginLoc, diag::note_reinterpret_updowncast_use_static)
974 << int(ReinterpretKind)
975 << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(BeginLoc, "static_cast");
976}
977
978/// CheckReinterpretCast - Check that a reinterpret_cast\<DestType\>(SrcExpr) is
979/// valid.
980/// Refer to C++ 5.2.10 for details. reinterpret_cast is typically used in code
981/// like this:
982/// char *bytes = reinterpret_cast\<char*\>(int_ptr);
983void CastOperation::CheckReinterpretCast() {
984 if (ValueKind == VK_RValue && !isPlaceholder(BuiltinType::Overload))
985 SrcExpr = Self.DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(SrcExpr.get());
986 else
987 checkNonOverloadPlaceholders();
988 if (SrcExpr.isInvalid()) // if conversion failed, don't report another error
989 return;
990
991 unsigned msg = diag::err_bad_cxx_cast_generic;
992 TryCastResult tcr =
993 TryReinterpretCast(Self, SrcExpr, DestType,
994 /*CStyle*/false, OpRange, msg, Kind);
995 if (tcr != TC_Success && msg != 0) {
996 if (SrcExpr.isInvalid()) // if conversion failed, don't report another error
997 return;
998 if (SrcExpr.get()->getType() == Self.Context.OverloadTy) {
999 //FIXME: &f<int>; is overloaded and resolvable
1000 Self.Diag(OpRange.getBegin(), diag::err_bad_reinterpret_cast_overload)
1001 << OverloadExpr::find(SrcExpr.get()).Expression->getName()
1002 << DestType << OpRange;
1003 Self.NoteAllOverloadCandidates(SrcExpr.get());
1004
1005 } else {
1006 diagnoseBadCast(Self, msg, CT_Reinterpret, OpRange, SrcExpr.get(),
1007 DestType, /*listInitialization=*/false);
1008 }
1009 }
1010
1011 if (isValidCast(tcr)) {
1012 if (Self.getLangOpts().allowsNonTrivialObjCLifetimeQualifiers())
1013 checkObjCConversion(Sema::CCK_OtherCast);
1014 DiagnoseReinterpretUpDownCast(Self, SrcExpr.get(), DestType, OpRange);
1015 } else {
1016 SrcExpr = ExprError();
1017 }
1018}

1021/// CheckStaticCast - Check that a static_cast\<DestType\>(SrcExpr) is valid.
1022/// Refer to C++ 5.2.9 for details. Static casts are mostly used for making
1023/// implicit conversions explicit and getting rid of data loss warnings.
1024void CastOperation::CheckStaticCast() {
1025 if (isPlaceholder()) {
1026 checkNonOverloadPlaceholders();
1027 if (SrcExpr.isInvalid())
1028 return;
1029 }
1030
1031 // This test is outside everything else because it's the only case where
1032 // a non-lvalue-reference target type does not lead to decay.
1033 // C++ 5.2.9p4: Any expression can be explicitly converted to type "cv void".
1034 if (DestType->isVoidType()) {
1035 Kind = CK_ToVoid;
1036
1037 if (claimPlaceholder(BuiltinType::Overload)) {
1038 Self.ResolveAndFixSingleFunctionTemplateSpecialization(SrcExpr,
1039 false, // Decay Function to ptr
1040 true, // Complain
1041 OpRange, DestType, diag::err_bad_static_cast_overload);
1042 if (SrcExpr.isInvalid())
1043 return;
1044 }
1045
1046 SrcExpr = Self.IgnoredValueConversions(SrcExpr.get());
1047 return;
1048 }
1049
1050 if (ValueKind == VK_RValue && !DestType->isRecordType() &&
1051 !isPlaceholder(BuiltinType::Overload)) {
1052 SrcExpr = Self.DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(SrcExpr.get());
1053 if (SrcExpr.isInvalid()) // if conversion failed, don't report another error
1054 return;
1055 }
1056
1057 unsigned msg = diag::err_bad_cxx_cast_generic;
1058 TryCastResult tcr
1059 = TryStaticCast(Self, SrcExpr, DestType, Sema::CCK_OtherCast, OpRange, msg,
1060 Kind, BasePath, /*ListInitialization=*/false);
1061 if (tcr != TC_Success && msg != 0) {
1062 if (SrcExpr.isInvalid())
1063 return;
1064 if (SrcExpr.get()->getType() == Self.Context.OverloadTy) {
1065 OverloadExpr* oe = OverloadExpr::find(SrcExpr.get()).Expression;
1066 Self.Diag(OpRange.getBegin(), diag::err_bad_static_cast_overload)
1067 << oe->getName() << DestType << OpRange
1068 << oe->getQualifierLoc().getSourceRange();
1069 Self.NoteAllOverloadCandidates(SrcExpr.get());
1070 } else {
1071 diagnoseBadCast(Self, msg, CT_Static, OpRange, SrcExpr.get(), DestType,
1072 /*listInitialization=*/false);
1073 }
1074 }
1075
1076 if (isValidCast(tcr)) {
1077 if (Kind == CK_BitCast)
1078 checkCastAlign();
1079 if (Self.getLangOpts().allowsNonTrivialObjCLifetimeQualifiers())
1080 checkObjCConversion(Sema::CCK_OtherCast);
1081 } else {
1082 SrcExpr = ExprError();
1083 }
1084}
1085
1086static bool IsAddressSpaceConversion(QualType SrcType, QualType DestType) {
1087 auto *SrcPtrType = SrcType->getAs<PointerType>();
1088 if (!SrcPtrType)
1089 return false;
1090 auto *DestPtrType = DestType->getAs<PointerType>();
1091 if (!DestPtrType)
1092 return false;
1093 return SrcPtrType->getPointeeType().getAddressSpace() !=
1094 DestPtrType->getPointeeType().getAddressSpace();
1095}
1096
1097/// TryStaticCast - Check if a static cast can be performed, and do so if
1098/// possible. If @p CStyle, ignore access restrictions on hierarchy casting
1099/// and casting away constness.
1100static TryCastResult TryStaticCast(Sema &Self, ExprResult &SrcExpr,
1101 QualType DestType,
1102 Sema::CheckedConversionKind CCK,
1103 SourceRange OpRange, unsigned &msg,
1104 CastKind &Kind, CXXCastPath &BasePath,
1105 bool ListInitialization) {
1106 // Determine whether we have the semantics of a C-style cast.
1107 bool CStyle
1108 = (CCK == Sema::CCK_CStyleCast || CCK == Sema::CCK_FunctionalCast);
1109
1110 // The order the tests is not entirely arbitrary. There is one conversion
1111 // that can be handled in two different ways. Given:
1112 // struct A {};
1113 // struct B : public A {
1114 // B(); B(const A&);
1115 // };
1116 // const A &a = B();
1117 // the cast static_cast<const B&>(a) could be seen as either a static
1118 // reference downcast, or an explicit invocation of the user-defined
1119 // conversion using B's conversion constructor.
1120 // DR 427 specifies that the downcast is to be applied here.
1121
1122 // C++ 5.2.9p4: Any expression can be explicitly converted to type "cv void".
1123 // Done outside this function.
1124
1125 TryCastResult tcr;
1126
1127 // C++ 5.2.9p5, reference downcast.
1128 // See the function for details.
1129 // DR 427 specifies that this is to be applied before paragraph 2.
1130 tcr = TryStaticReferenceDowncast(Self, SrcExpr.get(), DestType, CStyle,
1131 OpRange, msg, Kind, BasePath);
1132 if (tcr != TC_NotApplicable)
1133 return tcr;
1134
1135 // C++11 [expr.static.cast]p3:
1136 // A glvalue of type "cv1 T1" can be cast to type "rvalue reference to cv2
1137 // T2" if "cv2 T2" is reference-compatible with "cv1 T1".
1138 tcr = TryLValueToRValueCast(Self, SrcExpr.get(), DestType, CStyle, Kind,
1139 BasePath, msg);
1140 if (tcr != TC_NotApplicable)
1141 return tcr;
1142
1143 // C++ 5.2.9p2: An expression e can be explicitly converted to a type T
1144 // [...] if the declaration "T t(e);" is well-formed, [...].
1145 tcr = TryStaticImplicitCast(Self, SrcExpr, DestType, CCK, OpRange, msg,
1146 Kind, ListInitialization);
1147 if (SrcExpr.isInvalid())
1148 return TC_Failed;
1149 if (tcr != TC_NotApplicable)
1150 return tcr;
1151
1152 // C++ 5.2.9p6: May apply the reverse of any standard conversion, except
1153 // lvalue-to-rvalue, array-to-pointer, function-to-pointer, and boolean
1154 // conversions, subject to further restrictions.
1155 // Also, C++ 5.2.9p1 forbids casting away constness, which makes reversal
1156 // of qualification conversions impossible.
1157 // In the CStyle case, the earlier attempt to const_cast should have taken
1158 // care of reverse qualification conversions.
1159
1160 QualType SrcType = Self.Context.getCanonicalType(SrcExpr.get()->getType());
1161
1162 // C++0x 5.2.9p9: A value of a scoped enumeration type can be explicitly
1163 // converted to an integral type. [...] A value of a scoped enumeration type
1164 // can also be explicitly converted to a floating-point type [...].
1165 if (const EnumType *Enum = SrcType->getAs<EnumType>()) {
1166 if (Enum->getDecl()->isScoped()) {
1167 if (DestType->isBooleanType()) {
1168 Kind = CK_IntegralToBoolean;
1169 return TC_Success;
1170 } else if (DestType->isIntegralType(Self.Context)) {
1171 Kind = CK_IntegralCast;
1172 return TC_Success;
1173 } else if (DestType->isRealFloatingType()) {
1174 Kind = CK_IntegralToFloating;
1175 return TC_Success;
1176 }
1177 }
1178 }
1179
1180 // Reverse integral promotion/conversion. All such conversions are themselves
1181 // again integral promotions or conversions and are thus already handled by
1182 // p2 (TryDirectInitialization above).
1183 // (Note: any data loss warnings should be suppressed.)
1184 // The exception is the reverse of enum->integer, i.e. integer->enum (and
1185 // enum->enum). See also C++ 5.2.9p7.
1186 // The same goes for reverse floating point promotion/conversion and
1187 // floating-integral conversions. Again, only floating->enum is relevant.
1188 if (DestType->isEnumeralType()) {
1189 if (SrcType->isIntegralOrEnumerationType()) {
1190 Kind = CK_IntegralCast;
1191 return TC_Success;
1192 } else if (SrcType->isRealFloatingType()) {
1193 Kind = CK_FloatingToIntegral;
1194 return TC_Success;
1195 }
1196 }
1197
1198 // Reverse pointer upcast. C++ 4.10p3 specifies pointer upcast.
1199 // C++ 5.2.9p8 additionally disallows a cast path through virtual inheritance.
1200 tcr = TryStaticPointerDowncast(Self, SrcType, DestType, CStyle, OpRange, msg,
1201 Kind, BasePath);
1202 if (tcr != TC_NotApplicable)
1203 return tcr;
1204
1205 // Reverse member pointer conversion. C++ 4.11 specifies member pointer
1206 // conversion. C++ 5.2.9p9 has additional information.
1207 // DR54's access restrictions apply here also.
1208 tcr = TryStaticMemberPointerUpcast(Self, SrcExpr, SrcType, DestType, CStyle,
1209 OpRange, msg, Kind, BasePath);
1210 if (tcr != TC_NotApplicable)
1211 return tcr;
1212
1213 // Reverse pointer conversion to void*. C++ 4.10.p2 specifies conversion to
1214 // void*. C++ 5.2.9p10 specifies additional restrictions, which really is
1215 // just the usual constness stuff.
1216 if (const PointerType *SrcPointer = SrcType->getAs<PointerType>()) {
1217 QualType SrcPointee = SrcPointer->getPointeeType();
1218 if (SrcPointee->isVoidType()) {
1219 if (const PointerType *DestPointer = DestType->getAs<PointerType>()) {
1220 QualType DestPointee = DestPointer->getPointeeType();
1221 if (DestPointee->isIncompleteOrObjectType()) {
1222 // This is definitely the intended conversion, but it might fail due
1223 // to a qualifier violation. Note that we permit Objective-C lifetime
1224 // and GC qualifier mismatches here.
1225 if (!CStyle) {
1226 Qualifiers DestPointeeQuals = DestPointee.getQualifiers();
1227 Qualifiers SrcPointeeQuals = SrcPointee.getQualifiers();
1228 DestPointeeQuals.removeObjCGCAttr();
1229 DestPointeeQuals.removeObjCLifetime();
1230 SrcPointeeQuals.removeObjCGCAttr();
1231 SrcPointeeQuals.removeObjCLifetime();
1232 if (DestPointeeQuals != SrcPointeeQuals &&
1233 !DestPointeeQuals.compatiblyIncludes(SrcPointeeQuals)) {
1234 msg = diag::err_bad_cxx_cast_qualifiers_away;
1235 return TC_Failed;
1236 }
1237 }
1238 Kind = IsAddressSpaceConversion(SrcType, DestType)
1239 ? CK_AddressSpaceConversion
1240 : CK_BitCast;
1241 return TC_Success;
1242 }
1243
1244 // Microsoft permits static_cast from 'pointer-to-void' to
1245 // 'pointer-to-function'.
1246 if (!CStyle && Self.getLangOpts().MSVCCompat &&
1247 DestPointee->isFunctionType()) {
1248 Self.Diag(OpRange.getBegin(), diag::ext_ms_cast_fn_obj) << OpRange;
1249 Kind = CK_BitCast;
1250 return TC_Success;
1251 }
1252 }
1253 else if (DestType->isObjCObjectPointerType()) {
1254 // allow both c-style cast and static_cast of objective-c pointers as
1255 // they are pervasive.
1256 Kind = CK_CPointerToObjCPointerCast;
1257 return TC_Success;
1258 }
1259 else if (CStyle && DestType->isBlockPointerType()) {
1260 // allow c-style cast of void * to block pointers.
1261 Kind = CK_AnyPointerToBlockPointerCast;
1262 return TC_Success;
1263 }
1264 }
1265 }
1266 // Allow arbitrary objective-c pointer conversion with static casts.
1267 if (SrcType->isObjCObjectPointerType() &&
1268 DestType->isObjCObjectPointerType()) {
1269 Kind = CK_BitCast;
1270 return TC_Success;
1271 }
1272 // Allow ns-pointer to cf-pointer conversion in either direction
1273 // with static casts.
1274 if (!CStyle &&
1275 Self.CheckTollFreeBridgeStaticCast(DestType, SrcExpr.get(), Kind))
1276 return TC_Success;
1277
1278 // See if it looks like the user is trying to convert between
1279 // related record types, and select a better diagnostic if so.
1280 if (auto SrcPointer = SrcType->getAs<PointerType>())
1281 if (auto DestPointer = DestType->getAs<PointerType>())
1282 if (SrcPointer->getPointeeType()->getAs<RecordType>() &&
1283 DestPointer->getPointeeType()->getAs<RecordType>())
1284 msg = diag::err_bad_cxx_cast_unrelated_class;
1285
1286 // We tried everything. Everything! Nothing works! :-(
1287 return TC_NotApplicable;
1288}
1289
1290/// Tests whether a conversion according to N2844 is valid.
1291TryCastResult TryLValueToRValueCast(Sema &Self, Expr *SrcExpr,
1292 QualType DestType, bool CStyle,
1293 CastKind &Kind, CXXCastPath &BasePath,
1294 unsigned &msg) {
1295 // C++11 [expr.static.cast]p3:
1296 // A glvalue of type "cv1 T1" can be cast to type "rvalue reference to
1297 // cv2 T2" if "cv2 T2" is reference-compatible with "cv1 T1".
1298 const RValueReferenceType *R = DestType->getAs<RValueReferenceType>();
1299 if (!R)
1300 return TC_NotApplicable;
1301
1302 if (!SrcExpr->isGLValue())
1303 return TC_NotApplicable;
1304
1305 // Because we try the reference downcast before this function, from now on
1306 // this is the only cast possibility, so we issue an error if we fail now.
1307 // FIXME: Should allow casting away constness if CStyle.
1308 bool DerivedToBase;
1309 bool ObjCConversion;
1310 bool ObjCLifetimeConversion;
1311 QualType FromType = SrcExpr->getType();
1312 QualType ToType = R->getPointeeType();
1313 if (CStyle) {
1314 FromType = FromType.getUnqualifiedType();
1315 ToType = ToType.getUnqualifiedType();
1316 }
1317
1318 Sema::ReferenceCompareResult RefResult = Self.CompareReferenceRelationship(
1319 SrcExpr->getBeginLoc(), ToType, FromType, DerivedToBase, ObjCConversion,
1320 ObjCLifetimeConversion);
1321 if (RefResult != Sema::Ref_Compatible) {
1322 if (CStyle || RefResult == Sema::Ref_Incompatible)
1323 return TC_NotApplicable;
1324 // Diagnose types which are reference-related but not compatible here since
1325 // we can provide better diagnostics. In these cases forwarding to
1326 // [expr.static.cast]p4 should never result in a well-formed cast.
1327 msg = SrcExpr->isLValue() ? diag::err_bad_lvalue_to_rvalue_cast
1328 : diag::err_bad_rvalue_to_rvalue_cast;
1329 return TC_Failed;
1330 }
1331
1332 if (DerivedToBase) {
1333 Kind = CK_DerivedToBase;
1334 CXXBasePaths Paths(/*FindAmbiguities=*/true, /*RecordPaths=*/true,
1335 /*DetectVirtual=*/true);
1336 if (!Self.IsDerivedFrom(SrcExpr->getBeginLoc(), SrcExpr->getType(),
1337 R->getPointeeType(), Paths))
1338 return TC_NotApplicable;
1339
1340 Self.BuildBasePathArray(Paths, BasePath);
1341 } else
1342 Kind = CK_NoOp;
1343
1344 return TC_Success;
1345}
1346
1347/// Tests whether a conversion according to C++ 5.2.9p5 is valid.
1348TryCastResult
1349TryStaticReferenceDowncast(Sema &Self, Expr *SrcExpr, QualType DestType,
1350 bool CStyle, SourceRange OpRange,
1351 unsigned &msg, CastKind &Kind,
1352 CXXCastPath &BasePath) {
1353 // C++ 5.2.9p5: An lvalue of type "cv1 B", where B is a class type, can be
1354 // cast to type "reference to cv2 D", where D is a class derived from B,
1355 // if a valid standard conversion from "pointer to D" to "pointer to B"
1356 // exists, cv2 >= cv1, and B is not a virtual base class of D.
1357 // In addition, DR54 clarifies that the base must be accessible in the
1358 // current context. Although the wording of DR54 only applies to the pointer
1359 // variant of this rule, the intent is clearly for it to apply to the this
1360 // conversion as well.
1361
1362 const ReferenceType *DestReference = DestType->getAs<ReferenceType>();
1363 if (!DestReference) {
1364 return TC_NotApplicable;
1365 }
1366 bool RValueRef = DestReference->isRValueReferenceType();
1367 if (!RValueRef && !SrcExpr->isLValue()) {
1368 // We know the left side is an lvalue reference, so we can suggest a reason.
1369 msg = diag::err_bad_cxx_cast_rvalue;
1370 return TC_NotApplicable;
1371 }
1372
1373 QualType DestPointee = DestReference->getPointeeType();
1374
1375 if (IsBadCheriReferenceCast(DestReference, SrcExpr, Self.getASTContext())) {
1376 msg = diag::err_bad_cxx_reference_cast_capability_qualifier;
1377 return TC_Failed;
1378 }
1379
1380 // FIXME: If the source is a prvalue, we should issue a warning (because the
1381 // cast always has undefined behavior), and for AST consistency, we should
1382 // materialize a temporary.
1383 return TryStaticDowncast(Self,
1384 Self.Context.getCanonicalType(SrcExpr->getType()),
1385 Self.Context.getCanonicalType(DestPointee), CStyle,
1386 OpRange, SrcExpr->getType(), DestType, msg, Kind,
1387 BasePath);
1388}
1389
1390/// Tests whether a conversion according to C++ 5.2.9p8 is valid.
1391TryCastResult
1392TryStaticPointerDowncast(Sema &Self, QualType SrcType, QualType DestType,
1393 bool CStyle, SourceRange OpRange,
1394 unsigned &msg, CastKind &Kind,
1395 CXXCastPath &BasePath) {
1396 // C++ 5.2.9p8: An rvalue of type "pointer to cv1 B", where B is a class
1397 // type, can be converted to an rvalue of type "pointer to cv2 D", where D
1398 // is a class derived from B, if a valid standard conversion from "pointer
1399 // to D" to "pointer to B" exists, cv2 >= cv1, and B is not a virtual base
1400 // class of D.
1401 // In addition, DR54 clarifies that the base must be accessible in the
1402 // current context.
1403
1404 const PointerType *DestPointer = DestType->getAs<PointerType>();
1405 if (!DestPointer) {
1406 return TC_NotApplicable;
1407 }
1408
1409 const PointerType *SrcPointer = SrcType->getAs<PointerType>();
1410 if (!SrcPointer) {
1411 msg = diag::err_bad_static_cast_pointer_nonpointer;
1412 return TC_NotApplicable;
1413 }
1414
1415 return TryStaticDowncast(Self,
1416 Self.Context.getCanonicalType(SrcPointer->getPointeeType()),
1417 Self.Context.getCanonicalType(DestPointer->getPointeeType()),
1418 CStyle, OpRange, SrcType, DestType, msg, Kind,
1419 BasePath);
1420}
1421
1422/// TryStaticDowncast - Common functionality of TryStaticReferenceDowncast and
1423/// TryStaticPointerDowncast. Tests whether a static downcast from SrcType to
1424/// DestType is possible and allowed.
1425TryCastResult
1426TryStaticDowncast(Sema &Self, CanQualType SrcType, CanQualType DestType,
1427 bool CStyle, SourceRange OpRange, QualType OrigSrcType,
1428 QualType OrigDestType, unsigned &msg,
1429 CastKind &Kind, CXXCastPath &BasePath) {
1430 // We can only work with complete types. But don't complain if it doesn't work
1431 if (!Self.isCompleteType(OpRange.getBegin(), SrcType) ||
1432 !Self.isCompleteType(OpRange.getBegin(), DestType))
1433 return TC_NotApplicable;
1434
1435 // Downcast can only happen in class hierarchies, so we need classes.
1436 if (!DestType->getAs<RecordType>() || !SrcType->getAs<RecordType>()) {
1437 return TC_NotApplicable;
1438 }
1439
1440 CXXBasePaths Paths(/*FindAmbiguities=*/true, /*RecordPaths=*/true,
1441 /*DetectVirtual=*/true);
1442 if (!Self.IsDerivedFrom(OpRange.getBegin(), DestType, SrcType, Paths)) {
1443 return TC_NotApplicable;
1444 }
1445
1446 // Target type does derive from source type. Now we're serious. If an error
1447 // appears now, it's not ignored.
1448 // This may not be entirely in line with the standard. Take for example:
1449 // struct A {};
1450 // struct B : virtual A {
1451 // B(A&);
1452 // };
1453 //
1454 // void f()
1455 // {
1456 // (void)static_cast<const B&>(*((A*)0));
1457 // }
1458 // As far as the standard is concerned, p5 does not apply (A is virtual), so
1459 // p2 should be used instead - "const B& t(*((A*)0));" is perfectly valid.
1460 // However, both GCC and Comeau reject this example, and accepting it would
1461 // mean more complex code if we're to preserve the nice error message.
1462 // FIXME: Being 100% compliant here would be nice to have.
1463
1464 // Must preserve cv, as always, unless we're in C-style mode.
1465 if (!CStyle && !DestType.isAtLeastAsQualifiedAs(SrcType)) {
1466 msg = diag::err_bad_cxx_cast_qualifiers_away;
1467 return TC_Failed;
1468 }
1469
1470 if (Paths.isAmbiguous(SrcType.getUnqualifiedType())) {
1471 // This code is analoguous to that in CheckDerivedToBaseConversion, except
1472 // that it builds the paths in reverse order.
1473 // To sum up: record all paths to the base and build a nice string from
1474 // them. Use it to spice up the error message.
1475 if (!Paths.isRecordingPaths()) {
1476 Paths.clear();
1477 Paths.setRecordingPaths(true);
1478 Self.IsDerivedFrom(OpRange.getBegin(), DestType, SrcType, Paths);
1479 }
1480 std::string PathDisplayStr;
1481 std::set<unsigned> DisplayedPaths;
1482 for (clang::CXXBasePath &Path : Paths) {
1483 if (DisplayedPaths.insert(Path.back().SubobjectNumber).second) {
1484 // We haven't displayed a path to this particular base
1485 // class subobject yet.
1486 PathDisplayStr += "\n ";
1487 for (CXXBasePathElement &PE : llvm::reverse(Path))
1488 PathDisplayStr += PE.Base->getType().getAsString() + " -> ";
1489 PathDisplayStr += QualType(DestType).getAsString();
1490 }
1491 }
1492
1493 Self.Diag(OpRange.getBegin(), diag::err_ambiguous_base_to_derived_cast)
1494 << QualType(SrcType).getUnqualifiedType()
1495 << QualType(DestType).getUnqualifiedType()
1496 << PathDisplayStr << OpRange;
1497 msg = 0;
1498 return TC_Failed;
1499 }
1500
1501 if (Paths.getDetectedVirtual() != nullptr) {
1502 QualType VirtualBase(Paths.getDetectedVirtual(), 0);
1503 Self.Diag(OpRange.getBegin(), diag::err_static_downcast_via_virtual)
1504 << OrigSrcType << OrigDestType << VirtualBase << OpRange;
1505 msg = 0;
1506 return TC_Failed;
1507 }
1508
1509 if (!CStyle) {
1510 switch (Self.CheckBaseClassAccess(OpRange.getBegin(),
1511 SrcType, DestType,
1512 Paths.front(),
1513 diag::err_downcast_from_inaccessible_base)) {
1514 case Sema::AR_accessible:
1515 case Sema::AR_delayed: // be optimistic
1516 case Sema::AR_dependent: // be optimistic
1517 break;
1518
1519 case Sema::AR_inaccessible:
1520 msg = 0;
1521 return TC_Failed;
1522 }
1523 }
1524
1525 Self.BuildBasePathArray(Paths, BasePath);
1526 Kind = CK_BaseToDerived;
1527 return TC_Success;
1528}
1529
1530/// TryStaticMemberPointerUpcast - Tests whether a conversion according to
1531/// C++ 5.2.9p9 is valid:
1532///
1533/// An rvalue of type "pointer to member of D of type cv1 T" can be
1534/// converted to an rvalue of type "pointer to member of B of type cv2 T",
1535/// where B is a base class of D [...].
1536///
1537TryCastResult
1538TryStaticMemberPointerUpcast(Sema &Self, ExprResult &SrcExpr, QualType SrcType,
1539 QualType DestType, bool CStyle,
1540 SourceRange OpRange,
1541 unsigned &msg, CastKind &Kind,
1542 CXXCastPath &BasePath) {
1543 const MemberPointerType *DestMemPtr = DestType->getAs<MemberPointerType>();
1544 if (!DestMemPtr)
1545 return TC_NotApplicable;
1546
1547 bool WasOverloadedFunction = false;
1548 DeclAccessPair FoundOverload;
1549 if (SrcExpr.get()->getType() == Self.Context.OverloadTy) {
1550 if (FunctionDecl *Fn
1551 = Self.ResolveAddressOfOverloadedFunction(SrcExpr.get(), DestType, false,
1552 FoundOverload)) {
1553 CXXMethodDecl *M = cast<CXXMethodDecl>(Fn);
1554 SrcType = Self.Context.getMemberPointerType(Fn->getType(),
1555 Self.Context.getTypeDeclType(M->getParent()).getTypePtr());
1556 WasOverloadedFunction = true;
1557 }
1558 }
1559
1560 const MemberPointerType *SrcMemPtr = SrcType->getAs<MemberPointerType>();
1561 if (!SrcMemPtr) {
1562 msg = diag::err_bad_static_cast_member_pointer_nonmp;
1563 return TC_NotApplicable;
1564 }
1565
1566 // Lock down the inheritance model right now in MS ABI, whether or not the
1567 // pointee types are the same.
1568 if (Self.Context.getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft()) {
1569 (void)Self.isCompleteType(OpRange.getBegin(), SrcType);
1570 (void)Self.isCompleteType(OpRange.getBegin(), DestType);
1571 }
1572
1573 // T == T, modulo cv
1574 if (!Self.Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(SrcMemPtr->getPointeeType(),
1575 DestMemPtr->getPointeeType()))
1576 return TC_NotApplicable;
1577
1578 // B base of D
1579 QualType SrcClass(SrcMemPtr->getClass(), 0);
1580 QualType DestClass(DestMemPtr->getClass(), 0);
1581 CXXBasePaths Paths(/*FindAmbiguities=*/true, /*RecordPaths=*/true,
1582 /*DetectVirtual=*/true);
1583 if (!Self.IsDerivedFrom(OpRange.getBegin(), SrcClass, DestClass, Paths))
1584 return TC_NotApplicable;
1585
1586 // B is a base of D. But is it an allowed base? If not, it's a hard error.
1587 if (Paths.isAmbiguous(Self.Context.getCanonicalType(DestClass))) {
1588 Paths.clear();
1589 Paths.setRecordingPaths(true);
1590 bool StillOkay =
1591 Self.IsDerivedFrom(OpRange.getBegin(), SrcClass, DestClass, Paths);
1592 assert(StillOkay);
1593 (void)StillOkay;
1594 std::string PathDisplayStr = Self.getAmbiguousPathsDisplayString(Paths);
1595 Self.Diag(OpRange.getBegin(), diag::err_ambiguous_memptr_conv)
1596 << 1 << SrcClass << DestClass << PathDisplayStr << OpRange;
1597 msg = 0;
1598 return TC_Failed;
1599 }
1600
1601 if (const RecordType *VBase = Paths.getDetectedVirtual()) {
1602 Self.Diag(OpRange.getBegin(), diag::err_memptr_conv_via_virtual)
1603 << SrcClass << DestClass << QualType(VBase, 0) << OpRange;
1604 msg = 0;
1605 return TC_Failed;
1606 }
1607
1608 if (!CStyle) {
1609 switch (Self.CheckBaseClassAccess(OpRange.getBegin(),
1610 DestClass, SrcClass,
1611 Paths.front(),
1612 diag::err_upcast_to_inaccessible_base)) {
1613 case Sema::AR_accessible:
1614 case Sema::AR_delayed:
1615 case Sema::AR_dependent:
1616 // Optimistically assume that the delayed and dependent cases
1617 // will work out.
1618 break;
1619
1620 case Sema::AR_inaccessible:
1621 msg = 0;
1622 return TC_Failed;
1623 }
1624 }
1625
1626 if (WasOverloadedFunction) {
1627 // Resolve the address of the overloaded function again, this time
1628 // allowing complaints if something goes wrong.
1629 FunctionDecl *Fn = Self.ResolveAddressOfOverloadedFunction(SrcExpr.get(),
1630 DestType,
1631 true,
1632 FoundOverload);
1633 if (!Fn) {
1634 msg = 0;
1635 return TC_Failed;
1636 }
1637
1638 SrcExpr = Self.FixOverloadedFunctionReference(SrcExpr, FoundOverload, Fn);
1639 if (!SrcExpr.isUsable()) {
1640 msg = 0;
1641 return TC_Failed;
1642 }
1643 }
1644
1645 Self.BuildBasePathArray(Paths, BasePath);
1646 Kind = CK_DerivedToBaseMemberPointer;
1647 return TC_Success;
1648}
1649
1650/// TryStaticImplicitCast - Tests whether a conversion according to C++ 5.2.9p2
1651/// is valid:
1652///
1653/// An expression e can be explicitly converted to a type T using a
1654/// @c static_cast if the declaration "T t(e);" is well-formed [...].
1655TryCastResult
1656TryStaticImplicitCast(Sema &Self, ExprResult &SrcExpr, QualType DestType,
1657 Sema::CheckedConversionKind CCK,
1658 SourceRange OpRange, unsigned &msg,
1659 CastKind &Kind, bool ListInitialization) {
1660 if (DestType->isRecordType()) {
1661 if (Self.RequireCompleteType(OpRange.getBegin(), DestType,
1662 diag::err_bad_dynamic_cast_incomplete) ||
1663 Self.RequireNonAbstractType(OpRange.getBegin(), DestType,
1664 diag::err_allocation_of_abstract_type)) {
1665 msg = 0;
1666 return TC_Failed;
1667 }
1668 }
1669
1670 InitializedEntity Entity = InitializedEntity::InitializeTemporary(DestType);
1671 InitializationKind InitKind
1672 = (CCK == Sema::CCK_CStyleCast)
1673 ? InitializationKind::CreateCStyleCast(OpRange.getBegin(), OpRange,
1674 ListInitialization)
1675 : (CCK == Sema::CCK_FunctionalCast)
1676 ? InitializationKind::CreateFunctionalCast(OpRange, ListInitialization)
1677 : InitializationKind::CreateCast(OpRange);
1678 Expr *SrcExprRaw = SrcExpr.get();
1679 // FIXME: Per DR242, we should check for an implicit conversion sequence
1680 // or for a constructor that could be invoked by direct-initialization
1681 // here, not for an initialization sequence.
1682 InitializationSequence InitSeq(Self, Entity, InitKind, SrcExprRaw);
1683
1684 // At this point of CheckStaticCast, if the destination is a reference,
1685 // or the expression is an overload expression this has to work.
1686 // There is no other way that works.
1687 // On the other hand, if we're checking a C-style cast, we've still got
1688 // the reinterpret_cast way.
1689 bool CStyle
1690 = (CCK == Sema::CCK_CStyleCast || CCK == Sema::CCK_FunctionalCast);
1691 if (InitSeq.Failed() && (CStyle || !DestType->isReferenceType()))
1692 return TC_NotApplicable;
1693
1694 ExprResult Result = InitSeq.Perform(Self, Entity, InitKind, SrcExprRaw);
1695 if (Result.isInvalid()) {
1696 msg = 0;
1697 return TC_Failed;
1698 }
1699
1700 if (InitSeq.isConstructorInitialization())
1701 Kind = CK_ConstructorConversion;
1702 else
1703 Kind = CK_NoOp;
1704
1705 SrcExpr = Result;
1706 return TC_Success;
1707}

1709/// TryConstCast - See if a const_cast from source to destination is allowed,
1710/// and perform it if it is.
1711static TryCastResult TryConstCast(Sema &Self, ExprResult &SrcExpr,
1712 QualType DestType, bool CStyle,
1713 unsigned &msg) {
1714 DestType = Self.Context.getCanonicalType(DestType);
1715 QualType SrcType = SrcExpr.get()->getType();
1716 bool NeedToMaterializeTemporary = false;
1717
1718 if (const ReferenceType *DestTypeTmp =DestType->getAs<ReferenceType>()) {
1719 // C++11 5.2.11p4:
1720 // if a pointer to T1 can be explicitly converted to the type "pointer to
1721 // T2" using a const_cast, then the following conversions can also be
1722 // made:
1723 // -- an lvalue of type T1 can be explicitly converted to an lvalue of
1724 // type T2 using the cast const_cast<T2&>;
1725 // -- a glvalue of type T1 can be explicitly converted to an xvalue of
1726 // type T2 using the cast const_cast<T2&&>; and
1727 // -- if T1 is a class type, a prvalue of type T1 can be explicitly
1728 // converted to an xvalue of type T2 using the cast const_cast<T2&&>.
1729
1730 if (isa<LValueReferenceType>(DestTypeTmp) && !SrcExpr.get()->isLValue()) {
1731 // Cannot const_cast non-lvalue to lvalue reference type. But if this
1732 // is C-style, static_cast might find a way, so we simply suggest a
1733 // message and tell the parent to keep searching.
1734 msg = diag::err_bad_cxx_cast_rvalue;
1735 return TC_NotApplicable;
1736 }
1737
1738 if (isa<RValueReferenceType>(DestTypeTmp) && SrcExpr.get()->isRValue()) {
1739 if (!SrcType->isRecordType()) {
1740 // Cannot const_cast non-class prvalue to rvalue reference type. But if
1741 // this is C-style, static_cast can do this.
1742 msg = diag::err_bad_cxx_cast_rvalue;
1743 return TC_NotApplicable;
1744 }
1745
1746 // Materialize the class prvalue so that the const_cast can bind a
1747 // reference to it.
1748 NeedToMaterializeTemporary = true;
1749 }
1750
1751 // It's not completely clear under the standard whether we can
1752 // const_cast bit-field gl-values. Doing so would not be
1753 // intrinsically complicated, but for now, we say no for
1754 // consistency with other compilers and await the word of the
1755 // committee.
1756 if (SrcExpr.get()->refersToBitField()) {
1757 msg = diag::err_bad_cxx_cast_bitfield;
1758 return TC_NotApplicable;
1759 }
1760
1761 if (IsBadCheriReferenceCast(DestTypeTmp, SrcExpr.get(),
1762 Self.getASTContext())) {
1763 msg = diag::err_bad_cxx_reference_cast_capability_qualifier;
1764 return TC_NotApplicable;
1765 }
1766
1767 DestType = Self.Context.getPointerType(DestTypeTmp->getPointeeType());
1768 SrcType = Self.Context.getPointerType(SrcType);
1769 }
1770
1771 // C++ 5.2.11p5: For a const_cast involving pointers to data members [...]
1772 // the rules for const_cast are the same as those used for pointers.
1773
1774 if (!DestType->isPointerType() &&
1775 !DestType->isMemberPointerType() &&
1776 !DestType->isObjCObjectPointerType()) {
1777 // Cannot cast to non-pointer, non-reference type. Note that, if DestType
1778 // was a reference type, we converted it to a pointer above.
1779 // The status of rvalue references isn't entirely clear, but it looks like
1780 // conversion to them is simply invalid.
1781 // C++ 5.2.11p3: For two pointer types [...]
1782 if (!CStyle)
1783 msg = diag::err_bad_const_cast_dest;
1784 return TC_NotApplicable;
1785 }
1786 if (DestType->isFunctionPointerType() ||
1787 DestType->isMemberFunctionPointerType()) {
1788 // Cannot cast direct function pointers.
1789 // C++ 5.2.11p2: [...] where T is any object type or the void type [...]
1790 // T is the ultimate pointee of source and target type.
1791 if (!CStyle)
1792 msg = diag::err_bad_const_cast_dest;
1793 return TC_NotApplicable;
1794 }
1795
1796 // C++ [expr.const.cast]p3:
1797 // "For two similar types T1 and T2, [...]"
1798 //
1799 // We only allow a const_cast to change cvr-qualifiers, not other kinds of
1800 // type qualifiers. (Likewise, we ignore other changes when determining
1801 // whether a cast casts away constness.)
1802 if (!Self.Context.hasCvrSimilarType(SrcType, DestType))
1803 return TC_NotApplicable;
1804
1805 if (NeedToMaterializeTemporary)
1806 // This is a const_cast from a class prvalue to an rvalue reference type.
1807 // Materialize a temporary to store the result of the conversion.
1808 SrcExpr = Self.CreateMaterializeTemporaryExpr(SrcExpr.get()->getType(),
1809 SrcExpr.get(),
1810 /*IsLValueReference*/ false);
1811
1812 return TC_Success;
1813}
1814
1815// Checks for undefined behavior in reinterpret_cast.
1816// The cases that is checked for is:
1817// *reinterpret_cast<T*>(&a)
1818// reinterpret_cast<T&>(a)
1819// where accessing 'a' as type 'T' will result in undefined behavior.
1820void Sema::CheckCompatibleReinterpretCast(QualType SrcType, QualType DestType,
1821 bool IsDereference,
1822 SourceRange Range) {
1823 unsigned DiagID = IsDereference ?
1824 diag::warn_pointer_indirection_from_incompatible_type :
1825 diag::warn_undefined_reinterpret_cast;
1826
1827 if (Diags.isIgnored(DiagID, Range.getBegin()))
1828 return;
1829
1830 QualType SrcTy, DestTy;
1831 if (IsDereference) {
1832 if (!SrcType->getAs<PointerType>() || !DestType->getAs<PointerType>()) {
1833 return;
1834 }
1835 SrcTy = SrcType->getPointeeType();
1836 DestTy = DestType->getPointeeType();
1837 } else {
1838 if (!DestType->getAs<ReferenceType>()) {
1839 return;
1840 }
1841 SrcTy = SrcType;
1842 DestTy = DestType->getPointeeType();
1843 }
1844
1845 // Cast is compatible if the types are the same.
1846 if (Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(DestTy, SrcTy)) {
1847 return;
1848 }
1849 // or one of the types is a char or void type
1850 if (DestTy->isAnyCharacterType() || DestTy->isVoidType() ||
1851 SrcTy->isAnyCharacterType() || SrcTy->isVoidType()) {
1852 return;
1853 }
1854 // or one of the types is a tag type.
1855 if (SrcTy->getAs<TagType>() || DestTy->getAs<TagType>()) {
1856 return;
1857 }
1858
1859 // FIXME: Scoped enums?
1860 if ((SrcTy->isUnsignedIntegerType() && DestTy->isSignedIntegerType()) ||
1861 (SrcTy->isSignedIntegerType() && DestTy->isUnsignedIntegerType())) {
1862 if (Context.getTypeSize(DestTy) == Context.getTypeSize(SrcTy)) {
1863 return;
1864 }
1865 }
1866
1867 Diag(Range.getBegin(), DiagID) << SrcType << DestType << Range;
1868}

1870static void DiagnoseCHERICallback(Sema &Self, SourceLocation Loc,
1871 QualType SrcType, QualType DestType) {
1872 bool SrcIsCallback = false;
1873 bool DestIsCallback = false;
1874 if (auto SrcPointer = dyn_cast<PointerType>(SrcType))
1875 if (auto SrcFnPTy = SrcPointer->getPointeeType()->getAs<FunctionType>())
1876 if (SrcFnPTy->getCallConv() == CC_CHERICCallback)
1877 SrcIsCallback = true;
1878 if (auto DestPointer = dyn_cast<PointerType>(DestType))
1879 if (auto DestFnPTy = DestPointer->getPointeeType()->getAs<FunctionType>())
1880 if (DestFnPTy->getCallConv() == CC_CHERICCallback)
1881 DestIsCallback = true;
1882 if (SrcIsCallback != DestIsCallback)
1883 Self.Diag(Loc, diag::err_cheri_invalid_callback_cast);
1884}

1886static void DiagnoseCHERIPtr(Sema &Self, Expr *SrcExpr, QualType DestType,
1887 CastKind &Kind, SourceRange &Range) {
1888 if (Kind != CK_BitCast)
1889 return;
1890
1891 const PointerType *SrcPtr = SrcExpr->getType()->getAs<PointerType>();
1892 const PointerType *DestPtr = DestType->getAs<PointerType>();
1893 if (SrcPtr && DestPtr && !SrcPtr->isCHERICapability() && !DestPtr->isCHERICapability()) {
1894 QualType SrcPointee = SrcPtr->getPointeeType();
1895 QualType DestPointee = DestPtr->getPointeeType();
1896
1897 // casts from char * and void * are implicitly allowed
1898 if (SrcPointee->isCharType() || SrcPointee->isVoidType())
1899 return;
1900
1901 if (!SrcPointee->isCHERICapabilityType(Self.Context, true) &&
1902 DestPointee->isCHERICapabilityType(Self.Context, true)) {
1903 CharUnits SrcAlign = Self.Context.getTypeAlignInChars(SrcPointee);
1904 CharUnits DestAlign = Self.Context.getTypeAlignInChars(DestPointee);
1905
1906 if (SrcAlign >= DestAlign)
1907 return;
1908
1909 Self.Diag(Range.getBegin(), diag::err_cheri_ptr_align)
1910 << SrcExpr->getType() << DestType
1911 << static_cast<unsigned>(SrcAlign.getQuantity())
1912 << static_cast<unsigned>(DestAlign.getQuantity())
1913 << Range << SrcExpr->getSourceRange();
1914 Self.Diag(Range.getEnd(), diag::note_cheri_ptr_align_fixit);
1915 }
1916 }

1945 // DestType.dump("is memaddr?");

1984/// Diagnose casts that change the calling convention of a pointer to a function
1985/// defined in the current TU.
1986static void DiagnoseCallingConvCast(Sema &Self, const ExprResult &SrcExpr,
1987 QualType DstType, SourceRange OpRange) {
1988 // Check if this cast would change the calling convention of a function
1989 // pointer type.
1990 QualType SrcType = SrcExpr.get()->getType();
1991 if (Self.Context.hasSameType(SrcType, DstType) ||
1992 !SrcType->isFunctionPointerType() || !DstType->isFunctionPointerType())
1993 return;
1994 const auto *SrcFTy =
1995 SrcType->castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType()->castAs<FunctionType>();
1996 const auto *DstFTy =
1997 DstType->castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType()->castAs<FunctionType>();
1998 CallingConv SrcCC = SrcFTy->getCallConv();
1999 CallingConv DstCC = DstFTy->getCallConv();
2000 if (SrcCC == DstCC)
2001 return;
2002
2003 // We have a calling convention cast. Check if the source is a pointer to a
2004 // known, specific function that has already been defined.
2005 Expr *Src = SrcExpr.get()->IgnoreParenImpCasts();
2006 if (auto *UO = dyn_cast<UnaryOperator>(Src))
2007 if (UO->getOpcode() == UO_AddrOf)
2008 Src = UO->getSubExpr()->IgnoreParenImpCasts();
2009 auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(Src);
2010 if (!DRE)
2011 return;
2012 auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(DRE->getDecl());
2013 if (!FD)
2014 return;
2015
2016 // Only warn if we are casting from the default convention to a non-default
2017 // convention. This can happen when the programmer forgot to apply the calling
2018 // convention to the function declaration and then inserted this cast to
2019 // satisfy the type system.
2020 CallingConv DefaultCC = Self.getASTContext().getDefaultCallingConvention(
2021 FD->isVariadic(), FD->isCXXInstanceMember());
2022 if (DstCC == DefaultCC || SrcCC != DefaultCC)
2023 return;
2024
2025 // Diagnose this cast, as it is probably bad.
2026 StringRef SrcCCName = FunctionType::getNameForCallConv(SrcCC);
2027 StringRef DstCCName = FunctionType::getNameForCallConv(DstCC);
2028 Self.Diag(OpRange.getBegin(), diag::warn_cast_calling_conv)
2029 << SrcCCName << DstCCName << OpRange;
2030
2031 // The checks above are cheaper than checking if the diagnostic is enabled.
2032 // However, it's worth checking if the warning is enabled before we construct
2033 // a fixit.
2034 if (Self.Diags.isIgnored(diag::warn_cast_calling_conv, OpRange.getBegin()))
2035 return;
2036
2037 // Try to suggest a fixit to change the calling convention of the function
2038 // whose address was taken. Try to use the latest macro for the convention.
2039 // For example, users probably want to write "WINAPI" instead of "__stdcall"
2040 // to match the Windows header declarations.
2041 SourceLocation NameLoc = FD->getFirstDecl()->getNameInfo().getLoc();
2042 Preprocessor &PP = Self.getPreprocessor();
2043 SmallVector<TokenValue, 6> AttrTokens;
2044 SmallString<64> CCAttrText;
2045 llvm::raw_svector_ostream OS(CCAttrText);
2046 if (Self.getLangOpts().MicrosoftExt) {
2047 // __stdcall or __vectorcall
2048 OS << "__" << DstCCName;
2049 IdentifierInfo *II = PP.getIdentifierInfo(OS.str());
2050 AttrTokens.push_back(II->isKeyword(Self.getLangOpts())
2051 ? TokenValue(II->getTokenID())
2052 : TokenValue(II));
2053 } else {
2054 // __attribute__((stdcall)) or __attribute__((vectorcall))
2055 OS << "__attribute__((" << DstCCName << "))";
2056 AttrTokens.push_back(tok::kw___attribute);
2057 AttrTokens.push_back(tok::l_paren);
2058 AttrTokens.push_back(tok::l_paren);
2059 IdentifierInfo *II = PP.getIdentifierInfo(DstCCName);
2060 AttrTokens.push_back(II->isKeyword(Self.getLangOpts())
2061 ? TokenValue(II->getTokenID())
2062 : TokenValue(II));
2063 AttrTokens.push_back(tok::r_paren);
2064 AttrTokens.push_back(tok::r_paren);
2065 }
2066 StringRef AttrSpelling = PP.getLastMacroWithSpelling(NameLoc, AttrTokens);
2067 if (!AttrSpelling.empty())
2068 CCAttrText = AttrSpelling;
2069 OS << ' ';
2070 Self.Diag(NameLoc, diag::note_change_calling_conv_fixit)
2071 << FD << DstCCName << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(NameLoc, CCAttrText);
2072}
2073
2074static void checkIntToPointerCast(bool CStyle, SourceLocation Loc,
2075 const Expr *SrcExpr, QualType DestType,
2076 Sema &Self) {
2077 QualType SrcType = SrcExpr->getType();
2078 ASTContext &Ctx = Self.getASTContext();
2079
2080 if (DestType->isCHERICapabilityType(Ctx, true) &&
2081 !SrcType->isCHERICapabilityType(Ctx, true) &&
2082 !SrcExpr->isIntegerConstantExpr(Ctx)) {
2083 Self.Diag(Loc, diag::warn_capability_no_provenance) << DestType;
2084 Self.Diag(Loc, diag::note_insert_intptr_fixit);
2085 }
2086
2087 // Not warning on reinterpret_cast, boolean, constant expressions, etc
2088 // are not explicit design choices, but consistent with GCC's behavior.
2089 // Feel free to modify them if you've reason/evidence for an alternative.
2090 if (CStyle && SrcType->isIntegralType(Self.Context) &&
2091 !SrcType->isBooleanType() && !SrcType->isEnumeralType() &&
2092 !SrcExpr->isIntegerConstantExpr(Self.Context) &&
2093 Ctx.getIntRange(DestType) > Ctx.getIntRange(SrcType)) {
2094 // Separate between casts to void* and non-void* pointers.
2095 // Some APIs use (abuse) void* for something like a user context,
2096 // and often that value is an integer even if it isn't a pointer itself.
2097 // Having a separate warning flag allows users to control the warning
2098 // for their workflow.
2099 unsigned Diag = DestType->isVoidPointerType() ?
2100 diag::warn_int_to_void_pointer_cast
2101 : diag::warn_int_to_pointer_cast;
2102 Self.Diag(Loc, Diag) << SrcType << DestType;
2103 }
2104}
