2106static bool fixOverloadedReinterpretCastExpr(Sema &Self, QualType DestType,
2107 ExprResult &Result) {
2108 // We can only fix an overloaded reinterpret_cast if
2109 // - it is a template with explicit arguments that resolves to an lvalue
2110 // unambiguously, or
2111 // - it is the only function in an overload set that may have its address
2112 // taken.
2113
2114 Expr *E = Result.get();
2115 // TODO: what if this fails because of DiagnoseUseOfDecl or something
2116 // like it?
2117 if (Self.ResolveAndFixSingleFunctionTemplateSpecialization(
2118 Result,
2119 Expr::getValueKindForType(DestType) == VK_RValue // Convert Fun to Ptr
2120 ) &&
2121 Result.isUsable())
2122 return true;
2123
2124 // No guarantees that ResolveAndFixSingleFunctionTemplateSpecialization
2125 // preserves Result.
2126 Result = E;
2127 if (!Self.resolveAndFixAddressOfOnlyViableOverloadCandidate(
2128 Result, /*DoFunctionPointerConversion=*/true))
2129 return false;
2130 return Result.isUsable();
2131}
2132
2133static TryCastResult TryReinterpretCast(Sema &Self, ExprResult &SrcExpr,
2134 QualType DestType, bool CStyle,
2135 SourceRange OpRange,
2136 unsigned &msg,
2137 CastKind &Kind) {
2138 bool IsLValueCast = false;
2139
2140 DestType = Self.Context.getCanonicalType(DestType);
2141 QualType SrcType = SrcExpr.get()->getType();
2142
2143 // Is the source an overloaded name? (i.e. &foo)
2144 // If so, reinterpret_cast generally can not help us here (13.4, p1, bullet 5)
2145 if (SrcType == Self.Context.OverloadTy) {
2146 ExprResult FixedExpr = SrcExpr;
2147 if (!fixOverloadedReinterpretCastExpr(Self, DestType, FixedExpr))
2148 return TC_NotApplicable;
2149
2150 assert(FixedExpr.isUsable() && "Invalid result fixing overloaded expr");
2151 SrcExpr = FixedExpr;
2152 SrcType = SrcExpr.get()->getType();
2153 }
2154
2155 if (const ReferenceType *DestTypeTmp = DestType->getAs<ReferenceType>()) {
2156 if (!SrcExpr.get()->isGLValue()) {
2157 // Cannot cast non-glvalue to (lvalue or rvalue) reference type. See the
2158 // similar comment in const_cast.
2159 msg = diag::err_bad_cxx_cast_rvalue;
2160 return TC_NotApplicable;
2161 }
2162
2163 if (!CStyle) {
2164 Self.CheckCompatibleReinterpretCast(SrcType, DestType,
2165 /*isDereference=*/false, OpRange);
2166 }
2167
2168 // C++ 5.2.10p10: [...] a reference cast reinterpret_cast<T&>(x) has the
2169 // same effect as the conversion *reinterpret_cast<T*>(&x) with the
2170 // built-in & and * operators.
2171
2172 const char *inappropriate = nullptr;
2173 switch (SrcExpr.get()->getObjectKind()) {
2174 case OK_Ordinary:
2175 break;
2176 case OK_BitField:
2177 msg = diag::err_bad_cxx_cast_bitfield;
2178 return TC_NotApplicable;
2179 // FIXME: Use a specific diagnostic for the rest of these cases.
2180 case OK_VectorComponent: inappropriate = "vector element"; break;
2181 case OK_ObjCProperty: inappropriate = "property expression"; break;
2182 case OK_ObjCSubscript: inappropriate = "container subscripting expression";
2183 break;
2184 }
2185 if (inappropriate) {
2186 Self.Diag(OpRange.getBegin(), diag::err_bad_reinterpret_cast_reference)
2187 << inappropriate << DestType
2188 << OpRange << SrcExpr.get()->getSourceRange();
2189 msg = 0; SrcExpr = ExprError();
2190 return TC_NotApplicable;
2191 }
2192
2193 if (IsBadCheriReferenceCast(DestTypeTmp, SrcExpr.get(), Self.getASTContext())) {
2194 msg = diag::err_bad_cxx_reference_cast_capability_qualifier;
2195 return TC_Failed;
2196 }
2197
2198 // This code does this transformation for the checked types.
2199 DestType = Self.Context.getPointerType(DestTypeTmp->getPointeeType());
2200 SrcType = Self.Context.getPointerType(SrcType);
2201
2202 IsLValueCast = true;
2203 }
2204
2205 // Canonicalize source for comparison.
2206 SrcType = Self.Context.getCanonicalType(SrcType);
2207
2208 const MemberPointerType *DestMemPtr = DestType->getAs<MemberPointerType>(),
2209 *SrcMemPtr = SrcType->getAs<MemberPointerType>();
2210 if (DestMemPtr && SrcMemPtr) {
2211 // C++ 5.2.10p9: An rvalue of type "pointer to member of X of type T1"
2212 // can be explicitly converted to an rvalue of type "pointer to member
2213 // of Y of type T2" if T1 and T2 are both function types or both object
2214 // types.
2215 if (DestMemPtr->isMemberFunctionPointer() !=
2216 SrcMemPtr->isMemberFunctionPointer())
2217 return TC_NotApplicable;
2218
2219 if (Self.Context.getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft()) {
2220 // We need to determine the inheritance model that the class will use if
2221 // haven't yet.
2222 (void)Self.isCompleteType(OpRange.getBegin(), SrcType);
2223 (void)Self.isCompleteType(OpRange.getBegin(), DestType);
2224 }
2225
2226 // Don't allow casting between member pointers of different sizes.
2227 if (Self.Context.getTypeSize(DestMemPtr) !=
2228 Self.Context.getTypeSize(SrcMemPtr)) {
2229 msg = diag::err_bad_cxx_cast_member_pointer_size;
2230 return TC_Failed;
2231 }
2232
2233 // C++ 5.2.10p2: The reinterpret_cast operator shall not cast away
2234 // constness.
2235 // A reinterpret_cast followed by a const_cast can, though, so in C-style,
2236 // we accept it.
2237 if (auto CACK =
2238 CastsAwayConstness(Self, SrcType, DestType, /*CheckCVR=*/!CStyle,
2239 /*CheckObjCLifetime=*/CStyle))
2240 return getCastAwayConstnessCastKind(CACK, msg);
2241
2242 // A valid member pointer cast.
2243 assert(!IsLValueCast);
2244 Kind = CK_ReinterpretMemberPointer;
2245 return TC_Success;
2246 }
2247
2248 // See below for the enumeral issue.
2249 if (SrcType->isNullPtrType() && DestType->isIntegralType(Self.Context)) {
2250 // C++0x 5.2.10p4: A pointer can be explicitly converted to any integral
2251 // type large enough to hold it. A value of std::nullptr_t can be
2252 // converted to an integral type; the conversion has the same meaning
2253 // and validity as a conversion of (void*)0 to the integral type.
2254 bool SrcIsCap = SrcType->isCHERICapabilityType(Self.Context);
2255 // In purecap ABI casting to uint64_t is fine as we want the pointer range
2256 uint64_t Size = SrcIsCap
2257 ? Self.Context.getTargetInfo().getPointerRangeForCHERICapability()
2258 : Self.Context.getTypeSize(SrcType);
2259 if (Size > Self.Context.getTypeSize(DestType)) {
2260 msg = SrcIsCap ? diag::err_bad_cap_reinterpret_cast_small_int :
2261 diag::err_bad_reinterpret_cast_small_int;
2262 return TC_Failed;
2263 }
2264 Kind = SrcIsCap && !DestType->isIntCapType() ? CK_CHERICapabilityToAddress
2265 : CK_PointerToIntegral;
2266 return TC_Success;
2267 }
2268
2269 // Allow reinterpret_casts between vectors of the same size and
2270 // between vectors and integers of the same size.
2271 bool destIsVector = DestType->isVectorType();
2272 bool srcIsVector = SrcType->isVectorType();
2273 if (srcIsVector || destIsVector) {
2274 // The non-vector type, if any, must have integral type. This is
2275 // the same rule that C vector casts use; note, however, that enum
2276 // types are not integral in C++.
2277 if ((!destIsVector && !DestType->isIntegralType(Self.Context)) ||
2278 (!srcIsVector && !SrcType->isIntegralType(Self.Context)))
2279 return TC_NotApplicable;
2280
2281 // The size we want to consider is eltCount * eltSize.
2282 // That's exactly what the lax-conversion rules will check.
2283 if (Self.areLaxCompatibleVectorTypes(SrcType, DestType)) {
2284 Kind = CK_BitCast;
2285 return TC_Success;
2286 }
2287
2288 // Otherwise, pick a reasonable diagnostic.
2289 if (!destIsVector)
2290 msg = diag::err_bad_cxx_cast_vector_to_scalar_different_size;
2291 else if (!srcIsVector)
2292 msg = diag::err_bad_cxx_cast_scalar_to_vector_different_size;
2293 else
2294 msg = diag::err_bad_cxx_cast_vector_to_vector_different_size;
2295
2296 return TC_Failed;
2297 }
2298
2299 if (SrcType == DestType) {
2300 // C++ 5.2.10p2 has a note that mentions that, subject to all other
2301 // restrictions, a cast to the same type is allowed so long as it does not
2302 // cast away constness. In C++98, the intent was not entirely clear here,
2303 // since all other paragraphs explicitly forbid casts to the same type.
2304 // C++11 clarifies this case with p2.
2305 //
2306 // The only allowed types are: integral, enumeration, pointer, or
2307 // pointer-to-member types. We also won't restrict Obj-C pointers either.
2308 Kind = CK_NoOp;
2309 TryCastResult Result = TC_NotApplicable;
2310 if (SrcType->isIntegralOrEnumerationType() ||
2311 SrcType->isAnyPointerType() ||
2312 SrcType->isMemberPointerType() ||
2313 SrcType->isBlockPointerType()) {
2314 Result = TC_Success;
2315 }
2316 return Result;
2317 }
2318
2319 bool destIsPtr = DestType->isAnyPointerType() ||
2320 DestType->isBlockPointerType();
2321 bool srcIsPtr = SrcType->isAnyPointerType() ||
2322 SrcType->isBlockPointerType();
2323 if (!destIsPtr && !srcIsPtr) {
2324 // Except for std::nullptr_t->integer and lvalue->reference, which are
2325 // handled above, at least one of the two arguments must be a pointer.
2326 return TC_NotApplicable;
2327 }
2328
2329 if (DestType->isIntegralType(Self.Context)) {
2330 assert(srcIsPtr && "One type must be a pointer");
2331 // C++ 5.2.10p4: A pointer can be explicitly converted to any integral
2332 // type large enough to hold it; except in Microsoft mode, where the
2333 // integral type size doesn't matter (except we don't allow bool).
2334 bool MicrosoftException = Self.getLangOpts().MicrosoftExt &&
2335 !DestType->isBooleanType();
2336 bool SrcIsCap = SrcType->isCHERICapabilityType(Self.Context);
2337 // In purecap ABI casting to uint64_t is fine as we want the pointer range
2338 uint64_t Size = SrcIsCap
2339 ? Self.Context.getTargetInfo().getPointerRangeForCHERICapability()
2340 : Self.Context.getTypeSize(SrcType);
2341 if ((Size > Self.Context.getTypeSize(DestType)) && !MicrosoftException) {
2342 msg = SrcIsCap ? diag::err_bad_cap_reinterpret_cast_small_int :
2343 diag::err_bad_reinterpret_cast_small_int;
2344 return TC_Failed;
2345 }
2346 Kind = SrcIsCap && !DestType->isIntCapType() ? CK_CHERICapabilityToAddress
2347 : CK_PointerToIntegral;
2348 return TC_Success;
2349 }
2350
2351 if (SrcType->isIntegralOrEnumerationType()) {
2352 assert(destIsPtr && "One type must be a pointer");
2353 checkIntToPointerCast(CStyle, OpRange.getBegin(), SrcExpr.get(), DestType,
2354 Self);
2355 // C++ 5.2.10p5: A value of integral or enumeration type can be explicitly
2356 // converted to a pointer.
2357 // C++ 5.2.10p9: [Note: ...a null pointer constant of integral type is not
2358 // necessarily converted to a null pointer value.]
2359 Kind = CK_IntegralToPointer;
2360 return TC_Success;
2361 }
2362
2363 if (!destIsPtr || !srcIsPtr) {
2364 // With the valid non-pointer conversions out of the way, we can be even
2365 // more stringent.
2366 return TC_NotApplicable;
2367 }
2368
2369 // Cannot convert between block pointers and Objective-C object pointers.
2370 if ((SrcType->isBlockPointerType() && DestType->isObjCObjectPointerType()) ||
2371 (DestType->isBlockPointerType() && SrcType->isObjCObjectPointerType()))
2372 return TC_NotApplicable;
2373
2374 // C++ 5.2.10p2: The reinterpret_cast operator shall not cast away constness.
2375 // The C-style cast operator can.
2376 TryCastResult SuccessResult = TC_Success;
2377 if (auto CACK =
2378 CastsAwayConstness(Self, SrcType, DestType, /*CheckCVR=*/!CStyle,
2379 /*CheckObjCLifetime=*/CStyle))
2380 SuccessResult = getCastAwayConstnessCastKind(CACK, msg);
2381
2382 if (IsAddressSpaceConversion(SrcType, DestType)) {
2383 Kind = CK_AddressSpaceConversion;
2384 assert(SrcType->isPointerType() && DestType->isPointerType());
2385 if (!CStyle &&
2386 !DestType->getPointeeType().getQualifiers().isAddressSpaceSupersetOf(
2387 SrcType->getPointeeType().getQualifiers())) {
2388 SuccessResult = TC_Failed;
2389 }
2390 } else if (IsLValueCast) {
2391 Kind = CK_LValueBitCast;
2392 } else if (DestType->isObjCObjectPointerType()) {
2393 Kind = Self.PrepareCastToObjCObjectPointer(SrcExpr);
2394 } else if (DestType->isBlockPointerType()) {
2395 if (!SrcType->isBlockPointerType()) {
2396 Kind = CK_AnyPointerToBlockPointerCast;
2397 } else {
2398 Kind = CK_BitCast;
2399 }
2400 } else {
2401 Kind = CK_BitCast;
2402 }
2403
2404 // Any pointer can be cast to an Objective-C pointer type with a C-style
2405 // cast.
2406 if (CStyle && DestType->isObjCObjectPointerType()) {
2407 return SuccessResult;
2408 }
2409 if (CStyle)
2410 DiagnoseCastOfObjCSEL(Self, SrcExpr, DestType);
2411
2412 DiagnoseCallingConvCast(Self, SrcExpr, DestType, OpRange);
2413
2414 // Not casting away constness, so the only remaining check is for compatible
2415 // pointer categories.
2416
2417 if (SrcType->isFunctionPointerType()) {
2418 if (DestType->isFunctionPointerType()) {
2419 // C++ 5.2.10p6: A pointer to a function can be explicitly converted to
2420 // a pointer to a function of a different type.
2421 return SuccessResult;
2422 }
2423
2424 // C++0x 5.2.10p8: Converting a pointer to a function into a pointer to
2425 // an object type or vice versa is conditionally-supported.
2426 // Compilers support it in C++03 too, though, because it's necessary for
2427 // casting the return value of dlsym() and GetProcAddress().
2428 // FIXME: Conditionally-supported behavior should be configurable in the
2429 // TargetInfo or similar.
2430 Self.Diag(OpRange.getBegin(),
2431 Self.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 ?
2432 diag::warn_cxx98_compat_cast_fn_obj : diag::ext_cast_fn_obj)
2433 << OpRange;
2434 return SuccessResult;
2435 }
2436
2437 if (DestType->isFunctionPointerType()) {
2438 // See above.
2439 Self.Diag(OpRange.getBegin(),
2440 Self.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 ?
2441 diag::warn_cxx98_compat_cast_fn_obj : diag::ext_cast_fn_obj)
2442 << OpRange;
2443 return SuccessResult;
2444 }
2445
2446 // C++ 5.2.10p7: A pointer to an object can be explicitly converted to
2447 // a pointer to an object of different type.
2448 // Void pointers are not specified, but supported by every compiler out there.
2449 // So we finish by allowing everything that remains - it's got to be two
2450 // object pointers.
2451 return SuccessResult;
2452}
2453
2454static TryCastResult TryAddressSpaceCast(Sema &Self, ExprResult &SrcExpr,
2455 QualType DestType, bool CStyle,
2456 unsigned &msg) {
2457 if (!Self.getLangOpts().OpenCL)
2458 // FIXME: As compiler doesn't have any information about overlapping addr
2459 // spaces at the moment we have to be permissive here.
2460 return TC_NotApplicable;
2461 // Even though the logic below is general enough and can be applied to
2462 // non-OpenCL mode too, we fast-path above because no other languages
2463 // define overlapping address spaces currently.
2464 auto SrcType = SrcExpr.get()->getType();
2465 auto SrcPtrType = SrcType->getAs<PointerType>();
2466 if (!SrcPtrType)
2467 return TC_NotApplicable;
2468 auto DestPtrType = DestType->getAs<PointerType>();
2469 if (!DestPtrType)
2470 return TC_NotApplicable;
2471 auto SrcPointeeType = SrcPtrType->getPointeeType();
2472 auto DestPointeeType = DestPtrType->getPointeeType();
2473 if (SrcPointeeType.getAddressSpace() == DestPointeeType.getAddressSpace())
2474 return TC_NotApplicable;
2475 if (!DestPtrType->isAddressSpaceOverlapping(*SrcPtrType)) {
2476 msg = diag::err_bad_cxx_cast_addr_space_mismatch;
2477 return TC_Failed;
2478 }
2479 auto SrcPointeeTypeWithoutAS =
2480 Self.Context.removeAddrSpaceQualType(SrcPointeeType.getCanonicalType());
2481 auto DestPointeeTypeWithoutAS =
2482 Self.Context.removeAddrSpaceQualType(DestPointeeType.getCanonicalType());
2483 return Self.Context.hasSameType(SrcPointeeTypeWithoutAS,
2484 DestPointeeTypeWithoutAS)
2485 ? TC_Success
2486 : TC_NotApplicable;
2487}
2488
2489void CastOperation::checkAddressSpaceCast(QualType SrcType, QualType DestType) {
2490 // In OpenCL only conversions between pointers to objects in overlapping
2491 // addr spaces are allowed. v2.0 s6.5.5 - Generic addr space overlaps
2492 // with any named one, except for constant.
2493
2494 // Converting the top level pointee addrspace is permitted for compatible
2495 // addrspaces (such as 'generic int *' to 'local int *' or vice versa), but
2496 // if any of the nested pointee addrspaces differ, we emit a warning
2497 // regardless of addrspace compatibility. This makes
2498 // local int ** p;
2499 // return (generic int **) p;
2500 // warn even though local -> generic is permitted.
2501 if (Self.getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
2502 const Type *DestPtr, *SrcPtr;
2503 bool Nested = false;
2504 unsigned DiagID = diag::err_typecheck_incompatible_address_space;
2505 DestPtr = Self.getASTContext().getCanonicalType(DestType.getTypePtr()),
2506 SrcPtr = Self.getASTContext().getCanonicalType(SrcType.getTypePtr());
2507
2508 while (isa<PointerType>(DestPtr) && isa<PointerType>(SrcPtr)) {
2509 const PointerType *DestPPtr = cast<PointerType>(DestPtr);
2510 const PointerType *SrcPPtr = cast<PointerType>(SrcPtr);
2511 QualType DestPPointee = DestPPtr->getPointeeType();
2512 QualType SrcPPointee = SrcPPtr->getPointeeType();
2513 if (Nested ? DestPPointee.getAddressSpace() !=
2514 SrcPPointee.getAddressSpace()
2515 : !DestPPtr->isAddressSpaceOverlapping(*SrcPPtr)) {
2516 Self.Diag(OpRange.getBegin(), DiagID)
2517 << SrcType << DestType << Sema::AA_Casting
2518 << SrcExpr.get()->getSourceRange();
2519 if (!Nested)
2520 SrcExpr = ExprError();
2521 return;
2522 }
2523
2524 DestPtr = DestPPtr->getPointeeType().getTypePtr();
2525 SrcPtr = SrcPPtr->getPointeeType().getTypePtr();
2526 Nested = true;
2527 DiagID = diag::ext_nested_pointer_qualifier_mismatch;
2528 }
2529 }
2530}
2531
2532void CastOperation::CheckCXXCStyleCast(bool FunctionalStyle,
2533 bool ListInitialization) {
2534 assert(Self.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus);
2535
2536 // Handle placeholders.
2537 if (isPlaceholder()) {
2538 // C-style casts can resolve __unknown_any types.
2539 if (claimPlaceholder(BuiltinType::UnknownAny)) {
2540 SrcExpr = Self.checkUnknownAnyCast(DestRange, DestType,
2541 SrcExpr.get(), Kind,
2542 ValueKind, BasePath);
2543 return;
2544 }
2545
2546 checkNonOverloadPlaceholders();
2547 if (SrcExpr.isInvalid())
2548 return;
2549 }
2550
2551 // C++ 5.2.9p4: Any expression can be explicitly converted to type "cv void".
2552 // This test is outside everything else because it's the only case where
2553 // a non-lvalue-reference target type does not lead to decay.
2554 if (DestType->isVoidType()) {
2555 Kind = CK_ToVoid;
2556
2557 if (claimPlaceholder(BuiltinType::Overload)) {
2558 Self.ResolveAndFixSingleFunctionTemplateSpecialization(
2559 SrcExpr, /* Decay Function to ptr */ false,
2560 /* Complain */ true, DestRange, DestType,
2561 diag::err_bad_cstyle_cast_overload);
2562 if (SrcExpr.isInvalid())
2563 return;
2564 }
2565
2566 SrcExpr = Self.IgnoredValueConversions(SrcExpr.get());
2567 return;
2568 }
2569
2570 // If the type is dependent, we won't do any other semantic analysis now.
2571 if (DestType->isDependentType() || SrcExpr.get()->isTypeDependent() ||
2572 SrcExpr.get()->isValueDependent()) {
2573 assert(Kind == CK_Dependent);
2574 return;
2575 }
2576
2577 if (ValueKind == VK_RValue && !DestType->isRecordType() &&
2578 !isPlaceholder(BuiltinType::Overload)) {
2579 SrcExpr = Self.DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(SrcExpr.get());
2580 if (SrcExpr.isInvalid())
2581 return;
2582 }
2583
2584 // AltiVec vector initialization with a single literal.
2585 if (const VectorType *vecTy = DestType->getAs<VectorType>())
2586 if (vecTy->getVectorKind() == VectorType::AltiVecVector
2587 && (SrcExpr.get()->getType()->isIntegerType()
2588 || SrcExpr.get()->getType()->isFloatingType())) {
2589 Kind = CK_VectorSplat;
2590 SrcExpr = Self.prepareVectorSplat(DestType, SrcExpr.get());
2591 return;
2592 }
2593
2594 // C++ [expr.cast]p5: The conversions performed by
2595 // - a const_cast,
2596 // - a static_cast,
2597 // - a static_cast followed by a const_cast,
2598 // - a reinterpret_cast, or
2599 // - a reinterpret_cast followed by a const_cast,
2600 // can be performed using the cast notation of explicit type conversion.
2601 // [...] If a conversion can be interpreted in more than one of the ways
2602 // listed above, the interpretation that appears first in the list is used,
2603 // even if a cast resulting from that interpretation is ill-formed.
2604 // In plain language, this means trying a const_cast ...
2605 // Note that for address space we check compatibility after const_cast.
2606 unsigned msg = diag::err_bad_cxx_cast_generic;
2607 TryCastResult tcr = TryConstCast(Self, SrcExpr, DestType,
2608 /*CStyle*/ true, msg);
2609 if (SrcExpr.isInvalid())
2610 return;
2611 if (isValidCast(tcr))
2612 Kind = CK_NoOp;
2613
2614 Sema::CheckedConversionKind CCK =
2615 FunctionalStyle ? Sema::CCK_FunctionalCast : Sema::CCK_CStyleCast;
2616 if (tcr == TC_NotApplicable) {
2617 tcr = TryAddressSpaceCast(Self, SrcExpr, DestType, /*CStyle*/ true, msg);
2618 if (SrcExpr.isInvalid())
2619 return;
2620
2621 if (isValidCast(tcr))
2622 Kind = CK_AddressSpaceConversion;
2623
2624 if (tcr == TC_NotApplicable) {
2625 // ... or if that is not possible, a static_cast, ignoring const, ...
2626 tcr = TryStaticCast(Self, SrcExpr, DestType, CCK, OpRange, msg, Kind,
2627 BasePath, ListInitialization);
2628 if (SrcExpr.isInvalid())
2629 return;
2630
2631 if (tcr == TC_NotApplicable) {
2632 // ... and finally a reinterpret_cast, ignoring const.
2633 tcr = TryReinterpretCast(Self, SrcExpr, DestType, /*CStyle*/ true,
2634 OpRange, msg, Kind);
2635 if (SrcExpr.isInvalid())
2636 return;
2637 }
2638 }
2639 }
2640
2641 if (Self.getLangOpts().allowsNonTrivialObjCLifetimeQualifiers() &&
2642 isValidCast(tcr))
2643 checkObjCConversion(CCK);
2644
2645 if (tcr != TC_Success && msg != 0) {
2646 if (SrcExpr.get()->getType() == Self.Context.OverloadTy) {
2647 DeclAccessPair Found;
2648 FunctionDecl *Fn = Self.ResolveAddressOfOverloadedFunction(SrcExpr.get(),
2649 DestType,
2650 /*Complain*/ true,
2651 Found);
2652 if (Fn) {
2653 // If DestType is a function type (not to be confused with the function
2654 // pointer type), it will be possible to resolve the function address,
2655 // but the type cast should be considered as failure.
2656 OverloadExpr *OE = OverloadExpr::find(SrcExpr.get()).Expression;
2657 Self.Diag(OpRange.getBegin(), diag::err_bad_cstyle_cast_overload)
2658 << OE->getName() << DestType << OpRange
2659 << OE->getQualifierLoc().getSourceRange();
2660 Self.NoteAllOverloadCandidates(SrcExpr.get());
2661 }
2662 } else {
2663 diagnoseBadCast(Self, msg, (FunctionalStyle ? CT_Functional : CT_CStyle),
2664 OpRange, SrcExpr.get(), DestType, ListInitialization);
2665 }
2666 }
2667
2668 if (isValidCast(tcr)) {
2669 if (Kind == CK_BitCast)
2670 checkCastAlign();
2671 } else {
2672 SrcExpr = ExprError();
2673 }
2674}
2675
2676/// DiagnoseBadFunctionCast - Warn whenever a function call is cast to a
2677/// non-matching type. Such as enum function call to int, int call to
2678/// pointer; etc. Cast to 'void' is an exception.
2679static void DiagnoseBadFunctionCast(Sema &Self, const ExprResult &SrcExpr,
2680 QualType DestType) {
2681 if (Self.Diags.isIgnored(diag::warn_bad_function_cast,
2682 SrcExpr.get()->getExprLoc()))
2683 return;
2684
2685 if (!isa<CallExpr>(SrcExpr.get()))
2686 return;
2687
2688 QualType SrcType = SrcExpr.get()->getType();
2689 if (DestType.getUnqualifiedType()->isVoidType())
2690 return;
2691 if ((SrcType->isAnyPointerType() || SrcType->isBlockPointerType())
2692 && (DestType->isAnyPointerType() || DestType->isBlockPointerType()))
2693 return;
2694 if (SrcType->isIntegerType() && DestType->isIntegerType() &&
2695 (SrcType->isBooleanType() == DestType->isBooleanType()) &&
2696 (SrcType->isEnumeralType() == DestType->isEnumeralType()))
2697 return;
2698 if (SrcType->isRealFloatingType() && DestType->isRealFloatingType())
2699 return;
2700 if (SrcType->isEnumeralType() && DestType->isEnumeralType())
2701 return;
2702 if (SrcType->isComplexType() && DestType->isComplexType())
2703 return;
2704 if (SrcType->isComplexIntegerType() && DestType->isComplexIntegerType())
2705 return;
2706
2707 Self.Diag(SrcExpr.get()->getExprLoc(),
2708 diag::warn_bad_function_cast)
2709 << SrcType << DestType << SrcExpr.get()->getSourceRange();
2710}
2711
2712/// Check the semantics of a C-style cast operation, in C.
2713void CastOperation::CheckCStyleCast() {
2714 assert(!Self.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus);
2715
2716 // C-style casts can resolve __unknown_any types.
2717 if (claimPlaceholder(BuiltinType::UnknownAny)) {
2718 SrcExpr = Self.checkUnknownAnyCast(DestRange, DestType,
2719 SrcExpr.get(), Kind,
2720 ValueKind, BasePath);
2721 return;
2722 }
2723
2724 // C99 6.5.4p2: the cast type needs to be void or scalar and the expression
2725 // type needs to be scalar.
2726 if (DestType->isVoidType()) {
2727 // We don't necessarily do lvalue-to-rvalue conversions on this.
2728 SrcExpr = Self.IgnoredValueConversions(SrcExpr.get());
2729 if (SrcExpr.isInvalid())
2730 return;
2731
2732 // Cast to void allows any expr type.
2733 Kind = CK_ToVoid;
2734 return;
2735 }
2736
2737 // Overloads are allowed with C extensions, so we need to support them.
2738 if (SrcExpr.get()->getType() == Self.Context.OverloadTy) {
2739 DeclAccessPair DAP;
2740 if (FunctionDecl *FD = Self.ResolveAddressOfOverloadedFunction(
2741 SrcExpr.get(), DestType, /*Complain=*/true, DAP))
2742 SrcExpr = Self.FixOverloadedFunctionReference(SrcExpr.get(), DAP, FD);
2743 else
2744 return;
2745 assert(SrcExpr.isUsable());
2746 }
2747 SrcExpr = Self.DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(SrcExpr.get());
2748 if (SrcExpr.isInvalid())
2749 return;
2750 QualType SrcType = SrcExpr.get()->getType();
2751
2752 assert(!SrcType->isPlaceholderType());
2753
2754 checkAddressSpaceCast(SrcType, DestType);
2755 if (SrcExpr.isInvalid())
2756 return;
2757
2758 if (Self.RequireCompleteType(OpRange.getBegin(), DestType,
2759 diag::err_typecheck_cast_to_incomplete)) {
2760 SrcExpr = ExprError();
2761 return;
2762 }
2763
2764 if (!DestType->isScalarType() && !DestType->isVectorType()) {
2765 const RecordType *DestRecordTy = DestType->getAs<RecordType>();
2766
2767 if (DestRecordTy && Self.Context.hasSameUnqualifiedType(DestType, SrcType)){
2768 // GCC struct/union extension: allow cast to self.
2769 Self.Diag(OpRange.getBegin(), diag::ext_typecheck_cast_nonscalar)
2770 << DestType << SrcExpr.get()->getSourceRange();
2771 Kind = CK_NoOp;
2772 return;
2773 }
2774
2775 // GCC's cast to union extension.
2776 if (DestRecordTy && DestRecordTy->getDecl()->isUnion()) {
2777 RecordDecl *RD = DestRecordTy->getDecl();
2778 if (CastExpr::getTargetFieldForToUnionCast(RD, SrcType)) {
2779 Self.Diag(OpRange.getBegin(), diag::ext_typecheck_cast_to_union)
2780 << SrcExpr.get()->getSourceRange();
2781 Kind = CK_ToUnion;
2782 return;
2783 } else {
2784 Self.Diag(OpRange.getBegin(), diag::err_typecheck_cast_to_union_no_type)
2785 << SrcType << SrcExpr.get()->getSourceRange();
2786 SrcExpr = ExprError();
2787 return;
2788 }
2789 }
2790
2791 // OpenCL v2.0 s6.13.10 - Allow casts from '0' to event_t type.
2792 if (Self.getLangOpts().OpenCL && DestType->isEventT()) {
2793 Expr::EvalResult Result;
2794 if (SrcExpr.get()->EvaluateAsInt(Result, Self.Context)) {
2795 llvm::APSInt CastInt = Result.Val.getInt();
2796 if (0 == CastInt) {
2797 Kind = CK_ZeroToOCLOpaqueType;
2798 return;
2799 }
2800 Self.Diag(OpRange.getBegin(),
2801 diag::err_opencl_cast_non_zero_to_event_t)
2802 << CastInt.toString(10) << SrcExpr.get()->getSourceRange();
2803 SrcExpr = ExprError();
2804 return;
2805 }
2806 }
2807
2808 // Reject any other conversions to non-scalar types.
2809 Self.Diag(OpRange.getBegin(), diag::err_typecheck_cond_expect_scalar)
2810 << DestType << SrcExpr.get()->getSourceRange();
2811 SrcExpr = ExprError();
2812 return;
2813 }
2814
2815 // The type we're casting to is known to be a scalar or vector.
2816
2817 // Require the operand to be a scalar or vector.
2818 if (!SrcType->isScalarType() && !SrcType->isVectorType()) {
2819 Self.Diag(SrcExpr.get()->getExprLoc(),
2820 diag::err_typecheck_expect_scalar_operand)
2821 << SrcType << SrcExpr.get()->getSourceRange();
2822 SrcExpr = ExprError();
2823 return;
2824 }
2825
2826 if (DestType->isExtVectorType()) {
2827 SrcExpr = Self.CheckExtVectorCast(OpRange, DestType, SrcExpr.get(), Kind);
2828 return;
2829 }
2830
2831 if (const VectorType *DestVecTy = DestType->getAs<VectorType>()) {
2832 if (DestVecTy->getVectorKind() == VectorType::AltiVecVector &&
2833 (SrcType->isIntegerType() || SrcType->isFloatingType())) {
2834 Kind = CK_VectorSplat;
2835 SrcExpr = Self.prepareVectorSplat(DestType, SrcExpr.get());
2836 } else if (Self.CheckVectorCast(OpRange, DestType, SrcType, Kind)) {
2837 SrcExpr = ExprError();
2838 }
2839 return;
2840 }
2841
2842 if (SrcType->isVectorType()) {
2843 if (Self.CheckVectorCast(OpRange, SrcType, DestType, Kind))
2844 SrcExpr = ExprError();
2845 return;
2846 }
2847
2848 // The source and target types are both scalars, i.e.
2849 // - arithmetic types (fundamental, enum, and complex)
2850 // - all kinds of pointers
2851 // Note that member pointers were filtered out with C++, above.
2852
2853 if (isa<ObjCSelectorExpr>(SrcExpr.get())) {
2854 Self.Diag(SrcExpr.get()->getExprLoc(), diag::err_cast_selector_expr);
2855 SrcExpr = ExprError();
2856 return;
2857 }
2858
2859 // If either type is a pointer, the other type has to be either an
2860 // integer or a pointer.
2861 if (!DestType->isArithmeticType()) {
2862 if (!SrcType->isIntegralType(Self.Context) && SrcType->isArithmeticType()) {
2863 Self.Diag(SrcExpr.get()->getExprLoc(),
2864 diag::err_cast_pointer_from_non_pointer_int)
2865 << SrcType << SrcExpr.get()->getSourceRange();
2866 SrcExpr = ExprError();
2867 return;
2868 }
2869 checkIntToPointerCast(/* CStyle */ true, OpRange.getBegin(), SrcExpr.get(),
2870 DestType, Self);
2871 } else if (!SrcType->isArithmeticType()) {
2872 if (!DestType->isIntegralType(Self.Context) &&
2873 DestType->isArithmeticType()) {
2874 Self.Diag(SrcExpr.get()->getBeginLoc(),
2875 diag::err_cast_pointer_to_non_pointer_int)
2876 << DestType << SrcExpr.get()->getSourceRange();
2877 SrcExpr = ExprError();
2878 return;
2879 }
2880 }
2881
2882 if (Self.getLangOpts().OpenCL &&
2883 !Self.getOpenCLOptions().isEnabled("cl_khr_fp16")) {
2884 if (DestType->isHalfType()) {
2885 Self.Diag(SrcExpr.get()->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_opencl_cast_to_half)
2886 << DestType << SrcExpr.get()->getSourceRange();
2887 SrcExpr = ExprError();
2888 return;
2889 }
2890 }
2891
2892 // ARC imposes extra restrictions on casts.
2893 if (Self.getLangOpts().allowsNonTrivialObjCLifetimeQualifiers()) {
2894 checkObjCConversion(Sema::CCK_CStyleCast);
2895 if (SrcExpr.isInvalid())
2896 return;
2897
2898 const PointerType *CastPtr = DestType->getAs<PointerType>();
2899 if (Self.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount && CastPtr) {
2900 if (const PointerType *ExprPtr = SrcType->getAs<PointerType>()) {
2901 Qualifiers CastQuals = CastPtr->getPointeeType().getQualifiers();
2902 Qualifiers ExprQuals = ExprPtr->getPointeeType().getQualifiers();
2903 if (CastPtr->getPointeeType()->isObjCLifetimeType() &&
2904 ExprPtr->getPointeeType()->isObjCLifetimeType() &&
2905 !CastQuals.compatiblyIncludesObjCLifetime(ExprQuals)) {
2906 Self.Diag(SrcExpr.get()->getBeginLoc(),
2907 diag::err_typecheck_incompatible_ownership)
2908 << SrcType << DestType << Sema::AA_Casting
2909 << SrcExpr.get()->getSourceRange();
2910 return;
2911 }
2912 }
2913 }
2914 else if (!Self.CheckObjCARCUnavailableWeakConversion(DestType, SrcType)) {
2915 Self.Diag(SrcExpr.get()->getBeginLoc(),
2916 diag::err_arc_convesion_of_weak_unavailable)
2917 << 1 << SrcType << DestType << SrcExpr.get()->getSourceRange();
2918 SrcExpr = ExprError();
2919 return;
2920 }
2921 }
2922
2923 DiagnoseCHERICallback(Self, SrcExpr.get()->getBeginLoc(), SrcType, DestType);
2924 DiagnoseCastOfObjCSEL(Self, SrcExpr, DestType);
2925 DiagnoseCallingConvCast(Self, SrcExpr, DestType, OpRange);
2926 DiagnoseBadFunctionCast(Self, SrcExpr, DestType);
2927 Kind = Self.PrepareScalarCast(SrcExpr, DestType);
2928 DiagnoseCHERIPtr(Self, SrcExpr.get(), DestType, Kind, OpRange);
2929
2930 if (SrcExpr.isInvalid())
2931 return;
2932
2933 if (Kind == CK_BitCast)
2934 checkCastAlign();
2935}
2936
2937/// DiagnoseCastQual - Warn whenever casts discards a qualifiers, be it either
2938/// const, volatile or both.
2939static void DiagnoseCastQual(Sema &Self, const ExprResult &SrcExpr,
2940 QualType DestType) {
2941 if (SrcExpr.isInvalid())
2942 return;
2943
2944 QualType SrcType = SrcExpr.get()->getType();
2945 if (!((SrcType->isAnyPointerType() && DestType->isAnyPointerType()) ||
2946 DestType->isLValueReferenceType()))
2947 return;
2948
2949 QualType TheOffendingSrcType, TheOffendingDestType;
2950 Qualifiers CastAwayQualifiers;
2951 if (CastsAwayConstness(Self, SrcType, DestType, true, false,
2952 &TheOffendingSrcType, &TheOffendingDestType,
2953 &CastAwayQualifiers) !=
2954 CastAwayConstnessKind::CACK_Similar)
2955 return;
2956
2957 // FIXME: 'restrict' is not properly handled here.
2958 int qualifiers = -1;
2959 if (CastAwayQualifiers.hasConst() && CastAwayQualifiers.hasVolatile()) {
2960 qualifiers = 0;
2961 } else if (CastAwayQualifiers.hasConst()) {
2962 qualifiers = 1;
2963 } else if (CastAwayQualifiers.hasVolatile()) {
2964 qualifiers = 2;
2965 }
2966 // This is a variant of int **x; const int **y = (const int **)x;
2967 if (qualifiers == -1)
2968 Self.Diag(SrcExpr.get()->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_cast_qual2)
2969 << SrcType << DestType;
2970 else
2971 Self.Diag(SrcExpr.get()->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_cast_qual)
2972 << TheOffendingSrcType << TheOffendingDestType << qualifiers;
2973}
2974
2975ExprResult Sema::BuildCStyleCastExpr(SourceLocation LPLoc,
2976 TypeSourceInfo *CastTypeInfo,
2977 SourceLocation RPLoc,
2978 Expr *CastExpr) {
2979 CastOperation Op(*this, CastTypeInfo->getType(), CastExpr);
2980 Op.DestRange = CastTypeInfo->getTypeLoc().getSourceRange();
2981 Op.OpRange = SourceRange(LPLoc, CastExpr->getEndLoc());
2982
2983 if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
2984 Op.CheckCXXCStyleCast(/*FunctionalStyle=*/ false,
2985 isa<InitListExpr>(CastExpr));
2986 } else {
2987 Op.CheckCStyleCast();
2988 }
2989
2990 if (Op.SrcExpr.isInvalid())
2991 return ExprError();
2992
2993 // -Wcast-qual
2994 DiagnoseCastQual(Op.Self, Op.SrcExpr, Op.DestType);
2995
2996 return Op.complete(CStyleCastExpr::Create(Context, Op.ResultType,
2997 Op.ValueKind, Op.Kind, Op.SrcExpr.get(),
2998 &Op.BasePath, CastTypeInfo, LPLoc, RPLoc));
2999}

3001ExprResult Sema::BuildCXXFunctionalCastExpr(TypeSourceInfo *CastTypeInfo,
3002 QualType Type,
3003 SourceLocation LPLoc,
3004 Expr *CastExpr,
3005 SourceLocation RPLoc) {
3006 assert(LPLoc.isValid() && "List-initialization shouldn't get here.");
3007 CastOperation Op(*this, Type, CastExpr);
3008 Op.DestRange = CastTypeInfo->getTypeLoc().getSourceRange();
3009 Op.OpRange = SourceRange(Op.DestRange.getBegin(), CastExpr->getEndLoc());
3010
3011 Op.CheckCXXCStyleCast(/*FunctionalStyle=*/true, /*ListInit=*/false);
3012 if (Op.SrcExpr.isInvalid())
3013 return ExprError();
3014
3015 auto *SubExpr = Op.SrcExpr.get();
3016 if (auto *BindExpr = dyn_cast<CXXBindTemporaryExpr>(SubExpr))
3017 SubExpr = BindExpr->getSubExpr();
3018 if (auto *ConstructExpr = dyn_cast<CXXConstructExpr>(SubExpr))
3019 ConstructExpr->setParenOrBraceRange(SourceRange(LPLoc, RPLoc));
3020
3021 return Op.complete(CXXFunctionalCastExpr::Create(Context, Op.ResultType,
3022 Op.ValueKind, CastTypeInfo, Op.Kind,
3023 Op.SrcExpr.get(), &Op.BasePath, LPLoc, RPLoc));
3024}

3026ExprResult Sema::BuildCheriToOrFromCap(SourceLocation LParenLoc,
3027 SourceLocation KeywordLoc, bool IsToCap,
3028 QualType DestTy, TypeSourceInfo *TSInfo,
3029 SourceLocation RParenLoc, Expr *SubExpr) {
3030 // NOTE: __cheri_tocap and __cheri_fromcap are no-ops in both the hybrid and
3031 // purecap ABI if both source and destination types are capabilities
3032 // and the types are compatible.
3033
3034 // Use getRealReferenceType() because getType() only returns T for T&
3035 const QualType SrcTy = SubExpr->getRealReferenceType(Context, false);
3036 // Dependent types not yet handled, would probably need a new AST node to
3037 // differentiate from normal C-style casts
3038 if (SrcTy->isDependentType()) {
3039 Diag(KeywordLoc, diag::err_cheri_to_from_cap_not_supported_in_templates)
3040 << IsToCap << SrcTy;
3041 return ExprError();
3042 }
3043
3044 // We don't included __uintcap_t here since it should be be allowed to use
3045 // a __cheri_{to,from}cap on __uintcap_t
3046 const bool SrcIsCap = SrcTy->isCHERICapabilityType(Context, false);
3047 const bool DestIsCap = DestTy->isCHERICapabilityType(Context, false);
3048 CastKind Kind = CK_NoOp;
3049 if (IsToCap) {
3050 // __cheri_tocap
3051 if (!SrcTy->isPointerType()) {
3052 Diag(SubExpr->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_cheri_to_from_cap_invalid_source_type)
3053 << SrcTy << IsToCap;
3054 return ExprError();
3055 }
3056 if (!DestIsCap) {
3057 Diag(TSInfo->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(),
3058 diag::err_cheri_to_from_cap_invalid_target_type) << DestTy << IsToCap;
3059 return ExprError();
3060 }
3061 // No-op if SrcTy is a capability
3062 if (!SrcIsCap)
3063 Kind = CK_PointerToCHERICapability;
3064
3065 } else {
3066 // __cheri_fromcap
3067 if (!SrcIsCap) {
3068 Diag(SubExpr->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_cheri_to_from_cap_invalid_source_type)
3069 << SrcTy << IsToCap;
3070 return ExprError();
3071 }
3072 if (!DestTy->isPointerType()) {
3073 Diag(TSInfo->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(),
3074 diag::err_cheri_to_from_cap_invalid_target_type) << DestTy << IsToCap;
3075 return ExprError();
3076 }
3077 // No-op if DestTy is a capability
3078 if (!DestIsCap)
3079 Kind = CK_CHERICapabilityToPointer;
3080 }
3081
3082 // C++ checks if the types are exactly the same -> this will fail because
3083 // capability and non-capability Type* are different instances
3084 //
3085 // Types compatible source:
3086 // if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
3087 // return hasSameType(LHS, RHS);
3088 // return !mergeTypes(LHS, RHS, false, CompareUnqualified).isNull();
3089
3090 if (!CheckCHERIAssignCompatible(DestTy, SrcTy, SubExpr)) {
3091 Diag(SubExpr->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_cheri_to_from_cap_unrelated_type)
3092 << IsToCap << SrcTy << DestTy;
3093 return ExprError();
3094 }
3095
3096 // Warn about no-op cheri casts.
3097 if (Kind == CK_NoOp) {
3098 Diag(KeywordLoc, diag::warn_cheri_to_from_cap_noop)
3099 << IsToCap << SrcTy << DestTy
3100 << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(SourceRange(LParenLoc, RParenLoc));
3101 // If we are casting to void*
3102 }
3103
3104 return CStyleCastExpr::Create(Context, DestTy, VK_RValue, Kind, SubExpr,
3105 nullptr, TSInfo, LParenLoc, RParenLoc);
3106}
3107
3108// Check if LHS and RHS are assign compatible for CHERI (ignoring capability
3109// qualifiers). Insert an implicit bitcast if necessary (when InsertBitCast is
3110// true - the default) and update RHSExpr to point to it.
3111//
3112// Two types LHS and RHS are assign compatible (ignoring capability qualifiers) if:
3113// - LHS == RHS
3114// - either of LHS or RHS is void*
3115//
3116// In the case of LHS being void*, an implicit bitcast from RHSExpr to void*
3117// will be inserted and RHSExpr updated to point to this ImplicitCastExpr.
3118bool Sema::CheckCHERIAssignCompatible(QualType LHS, QualType RHS, Expr *&RHSExpr, bool InsertBitCast) {
3119 // XXXAR: I had to modify mergeTypes() to add a IncludeCapabilityQualifier
3120 // flag because here we want to compare everything but the __capability
3121 // qualifier
3122 // XXXKG: I also extended mergeTypes() with a MergeVoidPtr flag to allow the
3123 // <-> void* case (and still get the checking of qualifiers).
3124 // XXXKG: Allow non-const to const assignment
3125 QualType MergedTy = Context.mergeTypes(
3126 LHS, RHS, /*OfBlockPointer=*/false, /*Unqualified=*/false,
3127 /*BlockReturnType=*/false, /*IncludeCapabilityQualifier=*/false,
3128 /*MergeVoidPtr=*/false, /*MergeLHSConst=*/false);
3129 if (MergedTy.isNull()) {
3130 // As a special case we allow changing the types if either:
3131 // - LHS or RHS is a pointer to void
3132 // - LHS has a const-qualified pointee type and the RHS pointee is not
3133 // const-qualified
3134 MergedTy = Context.mergeTypes(
3135 LHS, RHS, /*OfBlockPointer=*/false, /*Unqualified=*/false,
3136 /*BlockReturnType=*/false, /*IncludeCapabilityQualifier=*/false,
3137 /*MergeVoidPtr=*/true, /*MergeLHSConst=*/true);
3138 if (!MergedTy.isNull()) {
3139 if (InsertBitCast) {
3140 // Insert a CK_BitCast to ensure we don't crash during codegen (see
3141 // https://github.com/CTSRD-CHERI/clang/issues/178)
3142 bool RHSIsCap = RHS->isCHERICapabilityType(Context, false);
3143 QualType BitCastTy = Context.getPointerType(
3144 LHS->getAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType(),
3145 RHSIsCap ? ASTContext::PIK_Capability : ASTContext::PIK_Integer);
3146 RHSExpr = ImplicitCastExpr::Create(Context, BitCastTy, CK_BitCast,
3147 RHSExpr, nullptr, VK_RValue);
3148 }
3149 return true;
3150 }
3151 return false;
3152 }
3153 return true;
3154}
3155
3156ExprResult Sema::BuildCheriOffsetOrAddress(SourceLocation LParenLoc,
3157 SourceLocation KeywordLoc,
3158 bool IsOffsetCast, QualType
3159 DestTy, TypeSourceInfo *TSInfo,
3160 SourceLocation RParenLoc, Expr
3161 *SubExpr) {
3162
3163 CastKind Kind =
3164 IsOffsetCast ? CK_CHERICapabilityToOffset : CK_CHERICapabilityToAddress;
3165
3166 // Check the source type
3167 // Use getRealReferenceType() because getType() only returns T for T&
3168 QualType SrcTy = SubExpr->getRealReferenceType(Context, false);
3169 // Dependent types not yet handled, would probably need a new AST node to
3170 // differentiate from normal C-style casts
3171 if (SrcTy->isDependentType()) {
3172 Diag(KeywordLoc, diag::err_cheri_addr_offset_not_supported_in_templates)
3173 << IsOffsetCast << SrcTy;
3174 return ExprError();
3175 }
3176 // __cheri_offset and __cheri_addr is valid for __uintcap_t as well
3177 bool SrcIsCap = SrcTy->isCHERICapabilityType(Context, true);
3178 if (!SrcIsCap) {
3179 // Note: __cheri_addr can be used on plain pointers since otherwise it would
3180 // be very difficult to write code that compiles both in hybrid and in
3181 // purecap mode. However, the offset cast only makes sense for capabilities!
3182 // XXXAR: Currently, __cheri_addr is allowed on references. Should we allow
3183 // this without an address-of operator first?
3184 if (IsOffsetCast || (!SrcTy->isPointerType() && !SrcTy->isReferenceType() &&
3185 !SrcTy->isIntCapType())) {
3186 // XXXKG: What about functions?
3187 Diag(SubExpr->getBeginLoc(),
3188 diag::err_cheri_offset_addr_invalid_source_type)
3189 << SrcTy << IsOffsetCast;
3190 return ExprError();
3191 } else {
3192 // Casting from pointer to address in hybrid mode
3193 assert(!Context.getTargetInfo().areAllPointersCapabilities());
3194 Kind = CK_PointerToIntegral;
3195 }
3196 }
3197
3198 // Check the destination type:
3199 // For __cheri_addr, output a more specific error message if DestTy is an
3200 // integral pointer type
3201 if (!IsOffsetCast) {
3202 if (DestTy->isPointerType()) {
3203 Diag(SubExpr->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_cheri_addr_ptr_type)
3204 << DestTy << (int)DestTy->getAs<PointerType>()->isCHERICapability();
3205 return ExprError();
3206 }
3207 }
3208 // Otherwise just check that it is a non-enum integer type
3209 bool DestIsInt = DestTy->isIntegerType() && !DestTy->isEnumeralType();
3210 if (!DestIsInt) {
3211 Diag(SubExpr->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_cheri_offset_addr_invalid_target_type)
3212 << DestTy << IsOffsetCast;
3213 return ExprError();
3214 }
3215
3216 // Output warning about truncation if DestTy is smaller than CHERI cap pointer range
3217 auto& TI = Context.getTargetInfo();
3218 uint64_t PtrRange = TI.getPointerRangeForCHERICapability();
3219 uint64_t DestRange = Context.getTypeSize(DestTy);
3220 if (DestRange < PtrRange) {
3221 bool DestIsSigned = DestTy->isSignedIntegerOrEnumerationType();
3222 const char *minTy = TI.getTypeName(
3223 TI.getLeastIntTypeByWidth(PtrRange, DestIsSigned)
3224 );
3225 Diag(SubExpr->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_cheri_offset_addr_smaller_target_type)
3226 << DestTy << minTy << IsOffsetCast;
3227 }
3228
3229 return CStyleCastExpr::Create(Context, DestTy, VK_RValue, Kind, SubExpr,
3230 nullptr, TSInfo, LParenLoc, RParenLoc);
3231}
3232
3233ExprResult Sema::ActOnCheriCast(Scope *S, SourceLocation LParenLoc, tok::TokenKind Kind,
3234 SourceLocation KeywordLoc, ParsedType Type,
3235 SourceLocation RParenLoc, Expr *SubExpr) {
3236 if (Kind == tok::kw___cheri_cast) {
3237 Diag(KeywordLoc, diag::err_cheri_cast);
3238 return ExprError();
3239 }
3240 TypeSourceInfo *TSInfo = nullptr;
3241 QualType T = GetTypeFromParser(Type, &TSInfo);
3242 if (!TSInfo)
3243 TSInfo = Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(T, LParenLoc);
3244
3245 // Perform the default function/array to pointer decay first:
3246 ExprResult Decayed = DefaultFunctionArrayLvalueConversion(SubExpr);
3247 if (Decayed.isInvalid())
3248 return ExprError();
3249 SubExpr = Decayed.get();
3250
3251 switch (Kind) {
3252 case tok::kw___cheri_tocap:
3253 case tok::kw___cheri_fromcap:
3254 return BuildCheriToOrFromCap(LParenLoc, KeywordLoc,
3255 Kind == tok::kw___cheri_tocap, T,
3256 TSInfo, RParenLoc, SubExpr);
3257
3258 case tok::kw___cheri_offset:
3259 case tok::kw___cheri_addr:
3260 return BuildCheriOffsetOrAddress(LParenLoc, KeywordLoc,
3261 Kind == tok::kw___cheri_offset, T,
3262 TSInfo, RParenLoc, SubExpr);
3263
3264 default:
3265 llvm_unreachable("Unknown CHERI cast!");
3266 }
